(1, 20, 6, 11, 28, '834db8610f5ff6ef71d39ea5adcf68fb.jpeg', 'Manchester United ap', 'Manchester United have applied to the Football Association to set up a professional women\'s team in the second tier of the Women\'s Super League, the club announced on Wednesday.\r\n*\r\nWith many leading English clubs, including Manchester City, Chelsea, Arsenal and Liverpool, all having sides in Super League One, United was widely criticised for not having an adult women\'s team.\r\n*\r\n\"We are pleased to announce that the club intends to establish its first ever professional women\'s team,\" United executive vice chairman Ed Woodward said in a statement.\r\n*\r\n\"The Manchester United women\'s team must be built in the same image and with the same principles as the men\'s first team and offer academy players a clear route to top level football within the club.\"\r\n*\r\nOn Wednesday, a report was published according to which United are the leading English club when it comes to social media muscle, despite going through a difficult patch ever since Sir Alex Ferguson left the managerial position.\r\n\r\n                  ', '6', '2018-03-24', '2020-01-31 13:45:01', 'Active'),
(2, 20, 6, 9, 21, '11ea112d53abb3694b4006ec950c9619.jpeg', 'South Africa vs Aust', 'A good first session of Test cricket. Electing to bat, South Africa will be quite pleased with the outcome. They did lose a wicket early in the form of Aiden Markram but since then it has been a one-way traffic.\r\n* Not a lot happening for the bowlers and it\'s been an easing going for the pair of Amla and Elgar. The Australian bowlers tried their heart out but did not receive any assistance from the deck. *The pitch is looking like a batting beauty and the narrative won\'t change much unless the Aussie bowlers produce something magical. \r\n*\r\nLet\'s see how the afternoon session unfurls. Join us in a short while.                  ', '4', '2018-03-24', '2018-04-18 12:49:17', 'Active'),
(3, 20, 7, 19, 28, '455e429fcb4d57f1c72579a09970cac5.jpeg', 'You can try out game', 'Ever wanted to play a game first but unsure about downloading it? If yes, then here is some good news for you. After launching Instant apps, Google now has launched Google Play Instant games that allows you to play games first and then download it.*\r\n\r\nGoogle Play Instant allows you to simply tap on a game and play it first without having to install it first. Typically, you could play games only after installing the app from Play Store first.\r\n*\r\nSome of the games included in the Play Store collection are Clash Royale, Words with Friends, Solitaire, Mighty Battles and more. However, please note that you will not be given the entire game to play.\r\n*\r\n Jonathan Karmel told TechRadar that only a smaller version of the app can be played with Instant gameplay.\r\n*\r\nGoogle is changing the way we use our phones. The company launched Google Instant apps in year 2016. Similar to Instant gameplay, it allows you to try out apps first without having to install them first.\r\n*\r\nWith Instant apps, you can run apps on your Android phone without installing them first.\r\n*\r\nGoogle is also focussing on users who can\'t afford to buy a costly smartphone. The company launched Android Go OS to give a smart OS experience on entry-level phones.\r\n*\r\n Google\'s Android Go is basically for entry-level phones. The company last month also launched lightweight Google assistant to work on its Android Go OS. The company also has Go apps that are compatible with the OS. These apps consume less space and are less data hungry.\r\n*\r\nNow users can also access Google Assistant on Android Go. Users who have Android Go and apps running on their phone can ask Google voice assistant now. However, not all apps have been designed to support the assistant presently. *\r\nThe Google Assistant, for now supports smart home devices, reminders and Actions on Android Go.                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(4, 20, 7, 27, 28, '0211801ce88743c5faea33d109a0f3ee.jpg', 'OnePlus 6 might be t', 'OnePlus is drawing closer to the launch its 2018 flagship- OnePlus 6 in the second quarter of the year. \r\n*\r\nWe can expect the smartphone to launch sometime in June with a display notch, Snapdragon 845 processor, 8GB of RAM and 256 GB of internal storage. \r\n*\r\nRecent leaks now hint towards a CAD $749 price (approximately Rs. 37,736) point for the OnePlus 6 (8GB RAM/256 GB storage) model plus taxes.\r\n*\r\n If the leaked prices turn out to be true, OnePlus 6 will be priced similarly if not higher than the OnePlus 5T which is priced Rs. 37,999 (including taxes) for the 8GB RAM edition. To compare, the OnePlus 5T was launched in India at a starting price of Rs. 32,999 (6GB RAM) while in the US, the smartphone was launched at a starting price of US $499 (roughly Rs. 33,000).\r\n*\r\n Also read: OnePlus 6: All that we know about the upcoming flagship\r\n\r\nThe leaked image comes courtesy Chinese website named CNMO which pegs the upcoming OnePlus 6 with iPhone X, Samsung Galaxy S9+ and Huawei P20. The list also shows the prices of other phones like the iPhone X which carries the massive $1517 CAD (roughly Rs. 76,430) price tag while the Galaxy S9+ is said to be priced at $1,200 CAD (roughly Rs. 60,963).  \r\n*\r\nThe leaked image seems to come from a company presentation slide and also has specifications like Snapdragon 845 processor, 8GB of RAM, and 256GB storage listed.\r\n*\r\n The leaked slide also hints at dual camera setup where there will be a 16-megapixel sensor coupled with a 20-megapixel sensor.\r\n*\r\n The smartphone will come with a Dash Charge support. It is said to sport a 6.2-inch display with an 18:9 aspect ratio. \r\n ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(5, 20, 9, 29, 13, 'adcf114d68dd7c81986f73d6b52dc32b.jpg', 'Canara Bank Probatio', 'New Delhi: Canara Bank has declared the result of Probationary Officers (POs) recruitment to be done through Post Graduate Diploma in Banking and Finance (PGDBF). \r\n*\r\nThe candidates who had appeared for the exam on March 4, 2018 can log onto the official website canarabank.com to access the results.\r\n*\r\nHow to access the Canara Bank PO Results 2018:\r\n*\r\n- Open the above-mentioned website\r\n- Click on the CAREERS tab and then select the Recruitment option\r\n- A new page will open. Click on ‘RP-2/2017 - Recruitment of Probationary Officers in JMGS-I on completion of specially designed PGDBF Course’ link.\r\n*\r\n- Another page will open on your screen where you need to click on ‘RP 2/2017-Probationary Officers (PGDBF) – list of provisionally selected candidates for group discussion and interview New’ link\r\n*\r\n- The list of successful candidates will appear.\r\n\r\nThe successful candidates will have to clear the Group Discussion (GD) followed by the personal interview.\r\n*\r\nIn January this year, Canara Bank had released an official notification to recruit 450 probationary officers through its Specially Designed Post Graduate Diploma in Banking and Finance (PGDBF) course.\r\n*\r\n The candidates selected would be required to complete the course, which would be conducted either by Manipal Global Education Services Pvt Ltd., Bengaluru or NITTE Education International Pvt Ltd., Mangaluru.\r\n*\r\nOn completion of the course, successful candidates would be recruited by the bank in Junior Management Grade Scale I.\r\n*\r\nDetails of Vacancy\r\nTotal Vacancies: 450\r\nSeats reserved for Scheduled Tribe: 67\r\nSeats reserved for Scheduled Caste: 35\r\nSeats for OBC Category: 121\r\nSeats under General or Unreserved Category: 227                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(6, 20, 9, 30, 28, 'a68daa149433d3bf4c75f1f3bc55545f.jpg', 'CBSE Class 10th Soci', 'New Delhi: Central Board of Secondary Education, CBSE conducted the Class 10 Social Science paper today. The first reactions of the examination are out now. \r\n*\r\nAs per the experts who have gone through the paper as well as the students who have appeared in the examination, the CBSE Class X social studies paper was very easy.\r\n*\r\n Students state that the paper was based completely out of NCERT. Here are the first reactions of experts and students on the CBSE Class 10 SST examination 2018.\r\n*\r\nStarting with the students, the paper was claimed to be easy and direct. “It was very easy,” responded a student, excited about her performance in the examination. Another student nodded in agreement.\r\n*\r\n “The papers have been very easy but I was still scared for SSt. But it was very easy. I am hoping for very good marks.”\r\n*\r\nAnalysing the question paper, the experts said that the paper was very easy for all the students. Not only was the paper from NCERT, it was direct and there weren’t any questions that would confuse the students, noted a senior examiner. Another expert agreed and said that the essay type questions were all direct.\r\n*\r\n “Students may lose marks in the short answer questions but the long answer questions were all easy and direct. It was a paper where it is difficult for students to lose marks.\r\n*\r\n” Related News | CBSE Class Xth English Board Exam 2018 students to get 2 marks for wrong question, here is what officials say\r\n*\r\nTalking about the overall trend of the examination so far the teachers noted, “CBSE has taken good care of the fact that these students are appearing for such extensive examination for the first time. \r\n*\r\nThe batch that has written the class 10 board examination was practically writing such an extensive syllabus examination for the very first time in their academic life. As such, the papers were easy and direct. It would help students allay the fear of ‘board examinations’.”\r\n', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(7, 20, 9, 31, 13, 'b4bbf8331bff4443968f7e55d8e538c5.jpg', 'RRB Recruitment 2018', 'Railway Recruitment Board, RRB has released the recruitment notice CEN 02/2018 for filling 62,907 Group D posts across regional RRBs.\r\n*\r\n The application process went live on February 10, 2018, and would be available until March 12, 2018. Candidates in the age group of 18 – 31 years of age that meet the educational qualifications are eligible to apply for the posts.\r\n*\r\n Here are important instructions and steps for filling the online application form for RRB Group D recruitment 2018. Direct links for applying online for the advertised railways\' jobs are also provided below.\r\n*\r\nBefore applying, all candidates are advised to carefully go through the detailed centralised employment notification or CEN. The notification number for Group D posts is CEN 02/2018. Direct link to the detailed notification is also given below.\r\n*\r\n Candidates should check the list of detailed vacancies in various RRBs to match the vacancy to their respective qualification in that RRB before applying. Candidates can check the vacancy available in various RRBs on the link provided below. Please note, once the RRB has been selected and registration is completed, change of RRB will not be permitted under any circumstances.                   ', '1', '2018-03-24', '2018-04-15 14:07:05', 'Active'),
(8, 20, 5, 10, 13, '779994a990b7d17294fc290b5146e6e2.jpg', 'Ranveer Singh was fi', 'Bollywood fans go to crazy extents when it comes to following their favourite stars. While mostly the fans just want a selfie or an autograph, some cross all boundaries and end up offending the star.\r\n*\r\n One such incident happened with Ranveer Singh when he was once changing after a swim and a fan allegedly filmed him.\r\n*\r\nDuring a recent media interaction, Ranveer recounted an incident that happened with him and said, “I was in the changing room, buck naked.\r\n*\r\n I’m drying my hair in one of the stalls. I look and there’s a guy filming with his light on. I was like, ‘Light toh off kar leta, toh pakda nahi jaata’,” READ: Here\'s what Ranveer Singh admires the most in a performer\r\n*\r\nRanveer added “I ran across the changing room, in my condition, and I have shouted ‘Aye!’ Because of the way I have shouted, he has panicked and forgotten to run away. Can you imagine naked me going,\r\n*\r\n ‘Aye, Aye!’? I caught his arm and I grabbed the phone. Fortunately, I had that presence of mind. If that video came out… I had to destroy it. It goes to this extent almost every other day,”                  ', '1', '2018-03-24', '2018-04-14 15:21:19', 'Active'),
(9, 20, 5, 26, 29, '8a6be5c0c7e7f2fe9d3654d6e2cc0a0c.jpg', 'Rangasthalam trailer', 'The much awaited theatrical trailer of Rangasthalam starring Ram Charan and Samantha Akkineni was released by the makers today. And, we must say has quite a lot to offer. \r\n*\r\nThe story seems to follow the life of Chitti Babu (Ram Charan) who is a deaf engineer and his friend Kumar Babu (Aadhi) in a village called Rangasthalam. The two fight a power-hungry leader (Jagpathi Babu) with the help of a communist leader (Prakash Raj).\r\n*\r\nAnd, while this seems to be the backbone of the story,  Samantha will be seen as the village beauty, Rama Lakshmi. She plays the romantic interest of Ram Charan promising some cute and funny moments in this intense action drama. \r\n*\r\nWe just hope she has much more role in the film than being just a love interest.                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(10, 20, 5, 10, 13, '4afc8c11c46026497bf1164517423101.jpg', 'Ayushmann Khurrana a', 'Badhaai Ho stars Ayushmann Khurrana and Sanya Malhotra visited the Bennett University in Uttar Pradesh\'s Noida on March 22.\r\n*\r\n Ayushmann, handsome in a shirt and white pants and Sanya, chic in a black dress, interacted with students at the university and also posed for pictures. Badhaai Ho has been directed by Amit Sharma. \r\n*\r\nAyushmann and Sanya completed filming on Wednesday. (Also Read: It\'s a wrap for Ayushmann Khurrana and Sanya Malhotra starrer Badhaai Ho). \r\n*\r\nBennett University (@bennettuniv) is a research-driven University, promoted by The Times of India Group, India’s oldest and largest media house.\r\n\r\n                  ', '1', '2018-03-24', '2018-04-19 15:54:22', 'Active'),
(11, 20, 15, 15, 28, 'cfa5dd6fcf66225567de98238ffb1c56.jpg', 'KC Tyagi denies JD(U', 'JD(U) spokesperson KC Tyagi on Thursday rejected any link with the data analytics firm Cambridge Analytica, which is being probed for data theft, adding that his son’s firm Ovlene Business Intelligence (OBI) had only a work relationship with the British firm.\r\n*\r\n “There was only a work relationship between my son Amrish\'s company and Cambridge Analytica, there is no financial transaction or shareholding and everything is open to probe. JDU also has no links with this, neither did they promote us in 2010 polls,” Tyagi told the media on Thursday.\r\n*\r\n“JDU has no relation with Cambridge Analytica, its CEO has met neither Nitishji nor me. In any case, JD(U) is a socialist outfit and we stay away from such things, except for maybe Prashant Kishore ji helping us during last assembly polls,” Tyagi added.\r\n ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(12, 20, 15, 8, 29, '72e550ae529380d450a0c1f9ca3b440e.JPG', 'Yogi Adityanath gove', 'The Yogi Adityanath-led BJP government in Uttar Pradesh has begun a procedure to withdraw 131 cases in connection with the 2013 communal riots that broke out in Muzaffarnagar and Shamli, killing several people. \r\n*\r\nOut of the 131 cases registered, 13 are of murder and 11 are an attempt to murder cases. As per Indian Express, the cases that are being withdrawn have been registered under \"heinous\" crimes, as per relevant IPC sections, with a minimum punishment of seven years in jail. \r\n*\r\nAt least 62 people were killed and scores were displaced from their homes during the September 2013 violence. Around 1,400 people were involved in 503 cases that were registered,\r\n*\r\n after the communal riots, by the then ruling party led by Akhilesh Yadav. The decision to withdraw these cases were taken after khap leaders from Muzaffarnagar and Shamli met Chief Minister Adityanath on February 5 with a list of 179 cases                  ', '2', '2018-03-24', '2018-04-16 15:10:37', 'Active'),
(13, 20, 13, 32, 28, 'a2b29b22040a126573e7f6b498d04907.jpeg', 'Want to travel witho', 'here\'s nothing as amazing as having wanderlust, or an unquenchable thirst to travel. Exploring places, whether they are new or old, gives you the opportunity to relax, experience different cultures, and witness sights you\'ve never seen before.\r\n*\r\nA true traveller usually makes enough space in his or her life to make travel plans possible. What\'s more, recently, you might have heard of people even quitting their jobs to travel full-time. The reason behind this is that with full-time jobs, you might not get to travel as much as you want.\r\n*\r\nAlso read: 5 tips on how to save money while travelling\r\n\r\nHowever, that\'s not completely true. There are some easy ways to make your travel dreams come true, while holding a full-time job. All you have to do is to use these tips:\r\n*\r\n1. Plan ahead\r\n\r\nEvery job comes with a number of assigned vacation or off-days. You need to chalk out your travel plans well in time, and make sure your superiors at work approve of them.\r\n*\r\n2. Manage existing public holidays\r\n\r\nEven if you don\'t have enough vacation leaves, you could easily plan a good number of vacations throughout the year. How, you ask? Just manage your existing public holidays properly.\r\n*\r\n3. Cover locations near and far\r\n\r\nIt\'s not necessary that you travel to long-distant destinations to satiate your wanderlust. Half the fun in travelling is to discover places that haven\'t been explored well enough yet.\r\n\r\n Use every opportunity\r\n\r\nApart from planning trips on your own, you could also use every opportunity to travel that comes your way.\r\n\r\n\r\n                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(14, 20, 10, 18, 25, '3a453cd2674045fa486914ab96a71a7b.jpeg', 'Designers make winter look hot on the AIFW 2018 ra', 'The finale shows of Day 3 and Day 4 set the mood for party dressing as designers Shivan and Narresh and Namrata Joshipura showcased their collections at the recently concluded Amazon India Fashion Week autumn/winter 2018.\r\n*\r\nThe beachwear boys, Shivan and Narresh presented a range of destination wedding wear dresses, throws, saris, lehengas, of course, swimwear for women and men.\r\n*\r\nThe collection was inspired by the famous 17th century Japanese Edo art movement, combined with their visit to Seychelles. The ensembles were covered with printed digital artworks, and while they were certainly striking, some pieces left one desiring better construction.\r\n*\r\nHowever, the show was equally commanded by the latest Indian designer eyewear brand to hit the runway, Indie Eye. The range of sunnies were a treat to the creative viewer, as the shapes were refreshingly nanny and fashionable, for the sake of fashion. The unusual styles caught the attention of the fashion fraternity.                                                                        ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(16, 17, 1, 34, 28, '8f1a5b297f2518301ff9b48ff60754e5.jpeg', 'Ibrahim Dawood', 'Pakistan-based crime syndicate D-company has diversified in many other fields, US lawmakers were told.\r\n*\r\n\"D-company, like Mexican drug organisations, has diversified. They traffic weapons, counterfeit DVDs, and provide financial services through their extensive system of hawala operators,\" Dr Louise Shelley, Professor, Schar School of Policy and Government, said during a Congressional hearing organised by the Committee on House Financial Services Subcommittee on Terrorism and Illicit Finance.\r\n*\r\nD-Company is headed by fugitive Indian underworld don Dawood Ibrahim.\r\n*\r\nWanted in India for a series of high profile crimes and terrorist attacks in places like Mumbai, Ibrahim according to US and Indian officials is now based in Pakistan\'s Karachi city. However, Pakistani officials have denied his presence in their country.\r\n*\r\nIndia\'s sustained campaign against Dawood was finally acknowledged by the United States of America in 2003 when the US Treasury department declared him a global terrorist having links with Al-Qaeda. He also faces sanctions from the United Nations under its anti-terror resolution.\r\n*\r\nVindicating India\'s position that Pakistan has been sheltering Dawood, the US Treasury Department had said he was in Karachi and possessed a Pakistani passport under the individual category.\r\n*\r\nTestifying before the same Congressional sub-committee, Celina B. Realuyo, Professor of Practice, William J Perry Centre for Hemispheric Defence Studies, National Defence University, said a number of recent attacks in Kabul were planned and launched from safe havens in Pakistan.\r\n*\r\nThe year 2018 has already witnessed many deadly attacks.                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(17, 17, 1, 35, 28, 'd9f3284af0d9115a0afe6ba6e965b06a.jpeg', 'Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg ', '\r\nNow that Facebook owner Mark Zuckerberg has apologised to Facebook users for Cambridge Analytica\'s access to their data, sources confirmed that an expert panel from social media and legal field will be set by the Election Commission and seek a detail report within two days.*\r\n\r\nAfter receiving the report EC will discuss on that.\r\n*\r\nOP Rawat, Chief Election Commissioner, told the Indian Express that within a week the matter of EC\'s partnership with Facebook to encourage enrollment of young voters will be discussion at a Commission meeting. He also said that the EC is concerned over allegations of data being used to influence voters by building psychological profiles of voters.\r\n*\r\nOn March 17, it was discovered that political consultancy Cambridge Analytica had harvested private information of over 50 million Facebook users without their knowledge or consent. The revelation of this scandal also created problems for Facebook as it revealed how easy it is for Facebook to freely hand out personal details of their users.\r\n*\r\nThe data was allegedly obtained using a personality quiz wherein 3,20,000 Facebook users who took the quiz unknowingly granted access to not just their profiles, but also 160(each) of their friends\'.                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(18, 22, 4, 23, 13, 'da4b16437caa8b6575687bc5119866b6.jpg', 'PNB issued over 40,000 LoUs since 2011 ', ' The central government has informed the Rajya Sabha that the country’s second-largest lender Punjab National Bank issued over 41,170 Letters of Undertaking (LoUs) since 2011, the same year when the mega Rs 13,600 crore fraud started to pick up pace. \r\n*Addressing the Rajya Sabha, Jaitley on Thursday said PNB had issued a total of over 40,000 LoUs, of which LoUs valid for 180 days were issued over 20,000 times.  \r\n*\r\n\"PNB has apprised that 7,672 LoUs were issued with a validity of 90 days, 20,078 LoUs were issued with a validity of 180 days, 11,224 LoUs were issued with validity of 365 days, and 2,204 LoUs were issued with validity of more than 365 days,\" Jaitley informed the Rajya Sabha. *\r\n\"Further, PNB has informed that the details regarding money withdrawn from the foreign branch of the other banks against each LoU is presently not available as the matter is under investigation,\" he added.  \r\n*\r\nSoon after the PNB fraud came to the fore, government and its financial arms rushed to damage control mode, taking a slew of actions to limit mega frauds by defaulters. While LoUs have been banned for standard trade,\r\n *Individuals seeking loans above Rs 50 crore have also come under the scanner now, as their passport details will be required for sanctioning the loan. \r\n*Traders across sectors have already expressed their anger over the move, claiming that businesses would suffer greatly due to the move.  \r\n                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(19, 22, 4, 38, 28, 'bdc8461172e0d6493521fa15e48a4d5a.jpeg', 'Virat Kohli calls off Rs 34 crore deal for luxury ', 'Mumbai: Indian cricket team captain Virat Kohli has reportedly cancelled a Rs 34 crore deal for a luxury apartment in the Omkar 1973 project, which is located in the city’s Worli area, reported The Economic Times. \r\n*The cricketer was in talks to purchase the apartment being built by Omkar Realtors and Developers for Rs 34 crore but the deal for the 7,000 sq ft apartment on the 35th floor of Tower C has been cancelled.\r\n* The report suggested that a cancellation deed was prepared on March 20 and registered the next day.  \r\n\r\n*\r\nHere\'s why Virat Kohli is paying Rs 15 lakh rent per month\r\n*\r\nSources in the realty market told ET that Kohli is now looking to buy a penthouse between the city’s western suburbs of Bandra and Versova. While the exact reason for the cancellation remains unknown, the report hints that Kohli would soon strike another deal as he is currently living in a rented accommodation in Mumbai, where he is paying Rs 15 lakh rent every month.  \r\n*\r\nThe 29-year-old cricketer, who got married to his better half actor Anushka Sharma in December last year, rented the apartment in Mumbai as Omkar 1973 was reportedly being constructed. If reports are to be believed, the Indian cricket team skipper has rented the 2,675 square feet apartment on the 40th floor of Raheja Legend in Worli’s Dr Annie Besant Road for over two years.  \r\n\r\n                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(20, 22, 4, 23, 28, 'dc86a46c2a20476c3b6494a0bbaa7be2.JPG', 'Government allocates Rs 100 billion for ‘Modicare’', 'New Delhi: Soon after the Union Cabinet approved the government’s ambitious health care plan, it has come to light that at least Rs 100 billion has been allocated to the scheme, \r\n*\r\nwhich is believed to benefit at least 11 crore poor families. The same was confirmed on Thursday by Union Health Minister JP Nadda, who termed it as the biggest health care scheme in the world.\r\n* The national healthcare plan, dubbed ‘Modicare’,  would be a portable scheme which can be availed of anywhere in India. There will be no cap on family size and age while payments will be on package rates. \r\n*\r\nUnder the centrally-sponsored scheme, touted to be the world\'s largest government-funded healthcare programme, it is proposed to set up the Ayushman Bharat - National Health Protection Mission Council (AB-NHPMC), chaired by the Union health minister, apart from establishing the AB-NHPM Governing Board. \r\n*\r\n\"The benefits cover will also include pre and post-hospitalisation expenses. All pre-existing conditions will be covered from day one of the policy,\" an official statement said. \r\n\r\n                                    ', '2', '2018-03-24', '2018-04-18 13:59:58', 'Active'),
(21, 22, 8, 40, 24, 'c684b563e0b4b239f9cf2774f8ccde55.jpeg', 'Fears of trade war between US, China send global m', 'The rumblings of a global trade war sent shivers through stock and currency markets on Friday after U.S. President Donald Trump announced long-promised tariffs on Chinese goods and China retaliated with a pledge to fight to the end any such war.*\r\n\r\nTrump signed a presidential memorandum on Thursday that could impose tariffs on up to $60 billion of imports from China, although the measures have a 30-day consultation period.\r\n*\r\nInvestors fear that the U.S. measures could escalate into a trade war, with potentially dire consequences for the global economy.\r\n*\r\nBeijing urged the United States on Friday to \"pull back from the brink\".\r\n*\r\n\"China doesn\'t hope to be in a trade war, but is not afraid of engaging in one,\" the Chinese commerce ministry said in a statement.\r\n*\r\nOn Friday, China unveiled plans to impose tariffs on up to $3 billion of U.S. imports in retaliation against U.S. tariffs on Chinese steel and aluminium products.\r\n*\r\nMSCI\'s broadest index of Asia-Pacific shares outside Japan fell 2.1 percent as stocks across the region dropped.\r\n*\r\nShanghai shares were down 3.2 percent.                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(22, 22, 8, 39, 28, '45cc6d98583893a9466adbae82a4cfca.jpeg', 'Peace on border must for healthy bilateral relatio', 'Maintenance of peace in border areas is an \"important pre-requisite\" for further development of India-China relations, New Delhi underlined this view today at a meeting on India-China border affairs.*\r\n\r\nIn a statement, issued after the 11th round of the \"Working Mechanism on Consultation & Coordination for India-China Border Affairs\" (WMCC) here, the External Affairs Ministry also said various confidence-building measures aimed at further enhancing the level of mutual trust and understanding among border personnel were discussed.\r\n*\r\nAsserting that discussions were held in a \"friendly and cordial\" atmosphere, the ministry said, \"The two sides exchanged views on ways to improve border management.\r\n* We underlined that maintenance of peace and tranquillity in the India-China border areas is an important pre-requisite for the further development of bilateral relations.\"\r\n*\r\nBoth sides also agreed to explore the possibility of strengthening cooperation through exchange of visits and institutionalised dialogue mechanisms to promote better understanding and cooperation between the two defence forces, the ministry said.\r\n*\r\nThe WMCC was established in 2012 as an institutional mechanism for consultation and coordination for maintenance of peace and tranquillity in the India-China border areas, as well as to exchange views on strengthening communication and cooperation, including between their border security personnel.\r\n*\r\nThe Indian delegation was led by Pranay Verma, Joint Secretary (East Asia) in the MEA, while the Chinese team was led by Yi Xianliang, Director General, Department of Boundary & Oceanic Affairs in the Chinese foreign ministry.\r\n*\r\nThe two sides agreed to hold the next meeting of the WMCC at a mutually convenient time.\r\n                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(23, 22, 7, 19, 28, '4d0ab4280df4214dd4eeaad6035a6081.jpeg', 'Delete Facebook: It sounds terrible but the idea i', 'Delete Facebook is trending in the wake of the Cambridge Analytica scandal. A lot of people are talking about deleting their Facebook accounts after it came to light that Cambridge Analytica used Facebook-provided tools and harvested personal data of nearly 50 million users. \r\n*\r\nFacebook wouldn\'t term what happened a data breach, but for users it doesn\'t matter. Many of them are angry and are trending hashtags like #DeleteFacebook.\r\n*\r\nThe hashtag has surprisingly found a lot of support from many quarters, including from WhatsApp co-founder Brian Acton who sold his company to Facebook for $19 billion a few years ago. It\'s time, he tweeted in support of #DeleteFacebook.\r\n*\r\nNow this idea of deleting Facebook sounds ludicrous when you first listen to it. Facebook is such an integral part of life for so many people nowadays that it seems implausible that it can be deleted from phones. People live inside the Facebook app. For some it has become their entire social world.\r\n*\r\nBut just think about it for a few minutes. Ask yourself a few question, and you will realise that deleting Facebook is not actually such a bad idea. It is not as bad as it sounds. You may even, after a few days, not notice that there used to be something like Facebook in your phone and that it took hours and hours of your time. \r\n*\r\nWe believe we are addicted to Facebook, and to its utility as a platform where we can share stuff. But just take a step back, and you will realise that it\'s not your entire world.                  ', '1', '2018-03-24', '2022-04-09 12:59:00', 'Active'),
(24, 20, 10, 12, 23, '24e68a64d20a67fee225283c760d53ef.jpeg', 'Water retention: Symptoms, causes, treatment', 'We all know that approximately 70 per cent of the human body comprises of water, present both inside and outside of the cells.\r\n*\r\nOur organs, muscles and even bones have high water content. Water is the essence of our existence but sometimes our body holds on to too much of it. Such excessive fluid build-up in the body leads to water retention.\r\n*\r\n\"Sudden swelling, puffiness or bloating of feet, ankles, hands, fingers and face can seem like weight gain. But, when no amount of dieting or exercise helps and the swelling persists with pain, it can be water retention,\" said Dr. Pooja Chaudhary, Wellness Consultant, Healthians.\r\n*\r\nWhat is water retention?\r\n\r\nWater retention or fluid retention (medically known as edema) is defined as an excessive build-up of fluid in the circulatory system, body tissues or cavities in the body which can lead to swelling of the hands, feet, ankles and legs. Water retention or edema can be triggered by a lot of different things.\r\n*\r\nCauses of water retention: Water retention could be caused due to many reasons, some of the common ones include:\r\n*\r\nDiet: Salt (sodium) rich food which are mostly include the processed food like meat, crackers, chips, canned vegetables, soups, fast food and even soft drinks can cause water retention.                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(25, 20, 10, 12, 25, 'c7ed059ac83a98c4abdca337354d6d06.jpeg', 'This popular American coffee-chain will now give e', 'The struggle to get equal pay for all genders and races is one that the whole world is engaged in today, and there have been quite a few victories of late. In January 2018,\r\n*\r\n Iceland became the first country to make it illegal for men to earn more than women. And now, a popular American coffee-chain claims to have implemented equal pay for all its workers.\r\n*\r\nStarbucks, the international coffee-chain which started in Seattle, has announced that they have now achieved 100 per cent equal pay across the country.\r\n*\r\n\"Proud to announce we\'ve achieved 100% pay equity for all US partners-but the work isn\'t done,\"(sic) the company announced on Twitter. \"We\'re committed to and working on doing the same globally.\"\r\n\r\n ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(26, 20, 10, 18, 13, '2b11570a2c926f701ea0036c01d01690.jpg', '5 times Kangana Ranaut made saree look uber-cool', 'If it hadn\'t been for Kangana Ranaut, who rings in her 31st birthday today, we would never know how easy-breezy and stunningly comfortable sarees can look. \r\n*\r\nFrom donning pastel shades with cute prints to simply opting for quirky shoes, here\'s how Kangana Ranaut has redefined the idea of sarees for us.                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(27, 20, 7, 27, 28, '322748eec788ead2bf6ebf86511bf728.jpg', 'Vivo V9 launched in India at Rs 22,990: Full specs', 'Vivo launched the V9 with an iPhone X-like notch, dual rear cameras, a whopping 24-megapixel camera on the front, and the latest Android Oreo software, in India on Friday. \r\n*\r\nThe most striking aspect of the V9 is its design even though some may say that Vivo has taken it a little too far this time. The Vivo V9 looks a lot like a certain phone from a certain company that shares its name with a fruit that apparently keeps doctors away, both inside and out. But while that will cost you close to a lakh, you can get Vivo V9 for Rs 22,990.\r\n*\r\nThe V9, which seems to be a successor to the V7 that was launched in India in November last year, is a phone banking heavily on design and camera capabilities. Here\'s a closer look at the Vivo V9.\r\n*\r\nSpecifications:\r\n\r\nProcessor: The Vivo V9 is powered by a 2.2GHz octa-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 626 processor clubbed with Adreno 506GPU.\r\n*\r\nRAM: 4GB\r\n\r\nInternal storage: The Vivo V9 comes with 64GB of internal storage which is further expandable by up to 256GB via a dedicated micro-SD card slot.\r\n*\r\nScreen: The Vivo V9 comes with a 6.3-inch IPS LCD display with a full-HD+ resolution (2280x1080) and curved 2.5D glass (unspecified) on the front. Vivo is also offering a free screen guard that comes pre-installed on the V9.\r\n*\r\nRear camera: The Vivo V9 comes with a dual camera system on the rear consisting of a primary 16-megapixel sensor with f/2.0 aperture and a 5-megapixel secondary sensor for depth sensing to enable portrait photos. The dual camera system further comes with phase detection autofocus and LED flash. The V9 can shoot 4K videos.\r\n*\r\nFront camera: On the front, the V9 comes with a whopping 24-megapixel camera with screen flash (selfie light). The front camera can record 1080p videos.\r\n\r\nSoftware: The V9 runs Android 8.1 Oreo-based Funtouch OS 4.0 which is Vivo\'s custom skin.\r\n\r\nBattery: The Vivo V9 is backed by a 3,260mAh battery and includes a 10W charger in the box.\r\n*\r\nSpecial features:\r\n\r\n-- The most striking aspect of the V9 is its design even though some may say that Vivo has taken it a little too far this time. \r\n*\r\nThe V9 looks remarkably like Apple\'s premium flagship iPhone X, especially from the front. But while the iPhone X costs almost a lakh to own, the the Vivo V9 costs mere peanuts in comparison. Just like the iPhone X the V9 also comes with a near edge-to-edge screen with a notch up-top. \r\n*\r\nThe notch allows Vivo to offer a screen-to-body ratio of almost a 90 per cent even though the V9 has a slight chin at the bottom, something that the iPhone X is lacking.\r\n*\r\n-- The notch on-board the V9 ships sans any fancy hardware and houses just the earpiece, the selfie camera, an LED notification light, and regular sensors. The notch that\'s on-board the iPhone X comes with dedicated hardware to enable Face ID, a form of recognition, that\'s touted as fast and secure.\r\n*\r\n The V9, for the record, also supports face unlock but it\'s nothing like Face ID, and Vivo itself warns users it isn\'t as secure as a fingerprint scanner.\r\n\r\n*\r\n-- The Vivo V9 has a plastic body and has a rear-mounted fingerprint scanner and micro-USB for charging and data syncing. It\'s quite attractive to look at, the V9, and also it\'s ridiculously light. It measures 7.89mm in thickness and weighs in at 150 gram. \r\n*\r\nThe back has a matte glossy finish to it that sort of eases into the front something that enhances ergonomics. Vivo seems to have done a good job here: the V9 is a large phone on paper, but, pint-sized to hold and operate.\r\n*\r\n-- The Vivo V9 has an unusually tall screen and an unusual aspect ratio of 19:9. Vivo calls it Full View.\r\n\r\n-- Vivo is banking heavily on artificial intelligence to sell its new phone. The V9, it says, comes with AI Smart Engine to boost the phone\'s performance over time through smart storage management and app launching based on user behaviour. \r\n*\r\nThe V9, in addition, comes with AI Face Access that\'s touted to improve the accuracy of the face unlock feature, and AI Attention Sensing that can apparently recognize when the user is looking at the screen and reduces the volume of notifications accordingly.\r\n*\r\n-- The dual camera system on the V9 can help capture portrait shots or photos with blurry background. A feature called shot refocus will allow users to adjust the bokeh post taking a shot while ultra HDR will allow the dual camera system to take three images of a shot, then superimpose them, to result in supposedly clearer photos with better contrast and saturation.\r\n*\r\n-- Vivo says, the V9 cameras are enhanced by AI. The selfie camera, in particular, supports AI Face Beauty that, according to Vivo, uses machine learning to identify users\' age, sex and skin tone to aid in supposedly better selfies. Both the front as well as the rear cameras also support live stickers, much on the lines of what Samsung has been offering for some time now.\r\n*\r\nPrice and availability:\r\n\r\nThe Vivo V9 will be available for buying in Pearl Black, Champagne Gold and Sapphire Blue colour options offline and online exclusively from Amazon India from April 2 with pre-orders beginning from Friday itself at a price of Rs 22,990.\r\n\r\n                  ', '1', '2018-03-24', '2020-01-01 14:42:12', 'Active'),
(29, 20, 4, 23, 13, 'e82205bdbbd2e52fb494957e114fc33a.jpg', 'Hurry up, 700 tech jobs up for grabs at Flipkart', 'Mumbai: Homegrown ecommerce giant Flipkart has started its hiring process after two years of no additions to its teams. The Bengaluru-based company has created 700 new positions in the technology department to bring in the next phase of technology revolution with artificial intelligence-powered solutions.\r\n*\r\nAt present, the company is seeking data scientists, product solution engineers, technology programme managers, UI and UX designers, software programme developers, service delivery infrastructure and IT applications.\r\n*\r\nRead: How Walmart-Flipkart plans to take on Amazon in India\r\n\r\nAt the recently concluded campus recruitment round, Flipkart has also made offers to at least 20 students from the Indian School of Business (ISB), an HR consultant familiar with the matter told the Economic Times.  \r\n*\r\nA Flipkart spokesperson confirmed this to ET and said, “Flipkart is aggressively hiring in tech functions. Over 4/5th of all current open positions at Flipkart is for technology functions. Aggressive tech hiring is part of the company’s ‘AI for India’ programme, which leverages Flipkart’s strengths in tech and data to build scalable AI-powered solutions for the country.”\r\n*\r\nIn 2016, reports surfaced that former Flipkart chief executive Binny Bansal had asked human resources head Nitin Sethi to directly look at all hires at mid and senior levels. HR head Nitin Sethi had instructed all business heads to hire people only if it was \"absolutely necessary\" for the team, according to multiple reports.                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(30, 20, 5, 10, 13, '419e1fa00bfbe9aca804564c51b411c1.jpg', 'Hichki Movie Review: Rani Mukerji keeps her chin u', 'How well do you remember your school auditorium? The smell of polished wood; the dim-lit stage, the swirling dust? When Naina Mathur (Rani Mukerji) – once student, now teacher – returns to St. Notkers, she finds her memories invaded.\r\n*\r\n The auditorium, visibly worn out, now serves as a hideout for the rascals of ‘9F’.  They smoke bidis, deal out cards, flip through fashion magazines and occasionally break out in freestyle rap. \r\n*\r\nNaina has been tasked to handle this bunch, shepherd them through the mid-terms. \"Haklati hain? (she hiccups?)\" laughs one of the punksters, amused by the peculiar condition of their new teacher. “Bet she\'ll scoot in a day...” another throws in a 20.\r\n*\r\nNaina smiles from a distance. Someone is about to lose his money.\r\n\r\n\r\nDirected and Indianized by Sidharth P. Malhotra, Rani Mukerji\'s Hichki has the sweet bearings of a sunny social drama. It straddles a visible line between a mellow Chak De! India and a breezy Taare Zameen Par, occasionally finding its voice in the smallest of characters.\r\n*\r\n There isn\'t much invention or newness as such (the film is a remake of Peter Werner\'s Front of the Class, which in turn was based on Brad Cohen\'s biographical book on his experiences with Tourette\'s Syndrome), but there are moments that are worth your engagement.\r\n*\r\n What could have become a bland rehash of a ready-to-cook Hollywood script (like last year\'s Chef or Tubelight) is saved and sauced up by some great performances and an on-and-off attachment to realism—‘adhesion’ and ‘cohesion’, as Rani explains in a science class. Sample this: In one of the starting scenes, Naina shuts up a school principal at a job interview for picking on her symptoms – a nervous tic motion of the head followed by quick, guttural sounds – and metaphorically shames him for having a choppy mind.\r\n*\r\n In the next scene, however, we find her lying on a promising phone call by saying...\"Kuch nahi sir, mera kutta bhawnk raha hai...\" (Nothing sir, my dog is barking…).\r\n*\r\nIn all her might and power, Rani Mukerji breezes through her character in Hichki, but the familiarity of terrain – a rebellious woman braving raised eyebrows to heal the world – squeezes out any room for variation, like Christopher Nolan forcing Michael Caine to play a caretaker once again.\r\n*\r\nWhich is why Malhotra’s film banks heavily on the freshness of erstwhile child actor, Harsh Mayar. Remembered best as the kid from I Am Kamal, Harsh, now almost 20, is a rare charmer. \r\n*\r\nHe plays the seemingly-hardened gang leader of ‘9F’, a slum-kid named Aatish, who carries enough redness in his eyes to match the spark in his name.\r\n*\r\n Hair-spiked, shirt tucked out, Aatish watches over his buddies at the school playground, answers arrogance with a punch, and ogles shamelessly at the hot topper girl of \'9A\'. Even at such a fledging age, Harsh pays undivided attention to his character, emoting thoughtfully in every reaction shot but also ducking his head when Rani mentions \'final exams\'.\r\n*\r\n Others in his crew - the overweight rapper, the clueless dim-wit, the lean hustler, the upright Anne Marie - flesh out their parts convincingly well, so does acting maestro Neeraj Kabi as the trim and dapper student council head, Mr. Wadia.\r\n*\r\nPaving multiple textures on a predictable story, Hichki fails to glue it all together with its glib optimism, and blows up in the end like Wadia\'s beloved \'science project\', which Aatish guts in response to an insult.\r\n*\r\n As for the themes of disability and discrimination at the workplace, all of that fades away in the first half and becomes incidental, or at best metaphorical, to the main plot, which is really all about reinforcing the corny adage... ‘There are no bad students, only bad teachers.\'\r\n*\r\nOccupying a spacious weekend and releasing two days after Rani Mukerji\'s 40th birthday, Hichki is a digestible senior-school drama baked to the comforts of its target audience – families and children, teachers and students – and should entertain them thoroughly.\r\n*\r\n In an endless swamp of watery Hollywood reprisals, Hichki stands on its own and underlines with a chalk why...\'there are no bad remakes, only bad filmmakers.\'\r\n\r\n                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(31, 20, 5, 10, 13, '2c32ded47f8f4086b6ad985af5c2dade.jpg', 'Aamir Khan trolled for picking Hindu mythology Mahbhartha', 'While most of Aamir Khan fans were super excited that the actoor will be working on his dream project, Mahabharata finally, there were some miscreants who decided to turn this good news into hate mongering on social media. \r\n*\r\nYes, some Twiitter users have reprimanded Aamir for taking on role of Hindu God on screen. And this came as no shocker considering that movies have become an easy target for people to pick, debate and fight over. Movies like Sexy Durga and Deepika Padukone-Ranveer Singh\'s Padmaavat have gotten embroiled in controversies for no reason. \r\n*\r\nWith a Muslim superstar deciding to play a Hindu mythological character, there were going to be people online who\'d find a reason for their existence on this planet. So, don\'t be surprised if this film runs into trouble even ahead of being filmed.\r\n*\r\n But guess what, veteran Bollywood writer Javed Akhtar responded to one of the troublemakers on Twitter and schooled him, making us squeal in joy. Here take a look..                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(32, 20, 6, 9, 28, 'e6d182fc89b68352bf41bc177ca4e44d.jpg', 'IPL 2018: Delhi Daredevils welcome back Mohammed S', 'Indian pacer Mohammed Shami, whose wife alleged him of abuse, cheating and match-fixing, breathed a little easy on Thursday after the Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) waived off the match-fixing charges against him.\r\n*\r\n As a result of the wrong-doings that Hasin had accused Shami of, the pace bowler’s name was taken off the newly released Central Contract and his Indian Premier League (IPL) franchise Delhi Daredevils were also unsure of his participation in the current circumstances.\r\n*\r\n With the Anti-Corruption Unit clearing Shami of fixing charges, the Daredevils have confirmed the bowler\'s return in their squad.\r\n*\r\nOn hearing about BCCI’s decision to hand include him in the list of players in Central Contract with Grade B, Shami said that he was sure about being proven innocent. \"I was sure I would be proved innocent. I have always tried to give my 100 percent in the game and I will continue to do so,\" he said while speaking to ANI.\r\n*\r\nShami’s IPL franchise, Delhi Daredevils, had earlier expressed dilemma over the bowler’s participation in season 11. The management had confirmed that based on the report by ACU, a final call will be taken on Shami’s immediate career.\r\n*\r\nWith the charges now waived off, franchise CEO Hemant Dua confirmed of Shami’s inclusion in the squad. “With the ACU clearing Shami, we are all set to have him back in the team,\" Dua told Sportstar.\r\n*\r\nEven the official Twitter account of the Daredevils welcomed BCCI’s decision. “We\'re glad to hear the verdict! @MdShami11 has been cleared to play by the @BCCI,” the franchise tweeted.                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active');
