(33, 20, 8, 40, 24, 'bad676b760710441b56d1a6cf39be6ff.JPG', 'New NSA John Bolton once expressed concerns about ', 'Washington: US President Donald Trump on Friday fired National Security Adviser Lt General HR McMaster and replaced him with former UN Ambassador John Bolton in the latest shake-up in the White House. \r\n*\r\nTrump took to Twitter to announce the news. \"I am pleased to announce, that, effective 4/9/18, John Bolton will be my new National Security Adviser,\" he wrote. McMaster was US President\'s second national security adviser after Michael Flynn was dismissed last year for misleading Vice President Mike Pence in the Russian meddling case.  \r\n*\r\nThe newly appointed NSA Bolton had earlier expressed that he has grave concerns about Islamabad\'s nuclear arsenal. Last year, Bolton said if Pakistan\'s nuclear weapons fall into the hands of terrorists, the situation would be that of North Korea or Iran on steroids. Bolton tweeted, \"Pakistan is a nuclear power and if it were to tip into terrorist control it would be like #NorthKorea or #Iran on steroids.\" \r\n*\r\nConsidered the most powerful wing in the White House, the National Security Council is the one that drives the administration\'s national security agenda. The announcement of McMaster\'s ouster is one of the high-profile departures from White House since Trump has taken office. The announcement came days after Trump replaced secretary of state Rex Tillerson with CIA Director and his close ally Mike Pompeo. The move was in light of the upcoming top-level nuclear talks with North Korea leader Kim Jong Un. \r\n*\r\nDonald Trump and McMaster had mutually decided that the latter will resign as the NSA and will retire from the US Army after 34 years of service. The official said the two have been \"discussing this for some time. \r\n*\r\nThe timeline was expedited as they both felt it was important to have the new team in place, instead of constant speculation. This was not related to any one moment or incident, rather it was the result of ongoing conversations between the two\". \r\n\r\n                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(34, 20, 8, 39, 25, '41fa53510e2b029b2cd07a91036d96a7.jpg', 'Two Indian-origin brothers indicted in US for laun', 'New York: Two Indian-origin Canadian brothers were indicted by a US court for allegedly laundering more than $250 million in transactions by operating Internet-based unlicensed money service business. \r\n*\r\nFiroz and Ferhan Patel, who live in Montreal, were charged with a count of conspiracy to operate an unlicensed money transmitting business to violate anti-money laundering programme requirements. Another count of charges was money laundering conspiracy and operating an unlicensed money transmitting business in Columbia.  \r\n*\r\nIf convicted, the brother will a sentence of 25 years in jail, said US Attorney Jessie Liu and Special Agent in Charge of US Immigration and Customs Enforcement\'s Homeland Security Investigations Washington DC Patrick Lechleitner. Ferhan was arrested in Detroit on March 18 and remained held until further proceedings take place. Firoz is still on the run.  \r\n*\r\nLiu said, \"Money transmitting businesses are required to be registered federally and licensed in most states and jurisdictions, including the District of Columbia. Consumers should beware of those that do not follow these laws because they could be acting as a cover for other illegal activity,\" as quoted by news agency PTI. The indictment alleges that illegal activities took place from March 2012 till this year and the defendants are accused of breaking several federal laws.  \r\n*\r\nThe company is accused of processing millions from Ponzi schemes, child pornography rings, and other criminal enterprises. The brothers had opened bank accounts in the States and laundered their illegal transactions through these accounts.  \r\n\r\n                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(35, 20, 9, 28, 28, '2ad66db5be1a24039bf2d361392ded46.jpg', 'UPSC Combined Geo-Scientist and Geologist Examinat', 'New Delhi: The Union Public Service Commission (UPSC) has invited applications for Indian Economic Service and Indian Statistical Service Examination, 2018. Candidates are required to apply online only by using the website www.upsconline.nic.in. Last date for submission of applications is April 16, 2018 till 6 pm. The exam will be held on June 29, 2018.\r\n*\r\nELIGIBILITY CRITERIA\r\n\r\nA candidate must have attained the age of 21 years and must not have attained the age of 30 years on August 1, 2018 i.e he/she must have been born not earlier than August 2, 1988 and not later than August 1, 1997. However, people belonging to reserved category will get relaxation.\r\n*\r\nHOW TO APPLY\r\n\r\n Visit the above-mentioned website\r\n Click ‘Online application for various examinations of UPSC’ link\r\n A new page will open where you have to clink on ‘Click Here for PART I’ and ‘Click Here for Part II’\r\n Fill the application form and pay the fees.\r\n Download your form and take a printout for future reference\r\n*\r\nVACANCY DETAILS\r\n\r\nThere are 14 vacancies for Indian Economic Service and 32 for Indian Statistical Service.\r\n\r\nFEE\r\n\r\nCandidates are required to pay a fee of Rs 200 either by depositing the money in any Branch of SBI by cash or by using net banking facility of State Bank of India or by using Visa/Master/RuPay Credit/Debit Card.\r\n*\r\nIMPORTANT INSTRUCTIONS\r\n\r\nMobile phones, bluetooth or any other communication devices will not be allowed inside the premises where the examination would be conducted. Any infringement of these instructions shall entail disciplinary action including ban from future examinations. \r\n*\r\nThere will be penalty (negative marking) for wrong answers marked by a candidate in the objective type question papers.\r\n*\r\nThe eligible candidates shall be issued an e Admission Certificate three weeks before the commencement of the examination. The e-Admission Certificate will be made available in the UPSC website for downloading by candidates. No Admission Certificate will be sent by post.                                    ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(36, 23, 11, 42, 23, '318ea6dd4b43308044c64901798cd2bc.jpg', 'Aries', 'There are chances that today you will turn to your family for success and happiness, predicts Ganesha. Of course, your display will come at the cost of a small fortune. Later in the day, a platonic love affair may begin. Those already involved in a romantic relationship will encounter thrilling moments, says Ganesha.', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-04-20 11:54:46', 'Active'),
(37, 23, 11, 43, 23, '5f2f62ba0a2cf67a46dc920d15885a9d.jpg', 'Taurus ', 'This is a productive day to deal in money matters, foresees Ganesha. You will probably enjoy both money and muscle power in the afternoon. A necklace or pendant is awaiting your sweetheart, so surprise her. Caution: There is a risk of your money being swindled.                  ', '0', '2018-04-20', '2018-04-20 12:05:45', 'Active'),
(38, 23, 11, 44, 23, '026cdc6ad0d1a0ef5fa513d5e528fb2f.png', 'Gemini ', 'You may or may not be too open about it, but you love those around you. You can easily sacrifice your ego to ensure that the sentiments of the ones you love are not hurt. But this can take its toll. You are probably planning a trip today — business or pleasure, whatever the excuse may be, the idea is to take a break. In the evening, you will be in the company of people who share your views, says Ganesha.                  ', '0', '2018-04-20', '2018-04-20 12:05:30', 'Active'),
(39, 23, 11, 45, 23, 'd74c7de493ea16487ec24c0ed5dae386.png', 'cancer ', 'You have a gift. You come across as a very approachable and dependable person. It\'s this attribute that makes people want to work with you and trust you, says Ganesha. But today is another day, and you may want a break from helping people fight their daily battles and spending some quality time with your family members. You may even plan a trip with your family members.                  ', '0', '2018-04-20', '2018-04-20 12:05:13', 'Active'),
(40, 23, 11, 46, 23, '83d6bd188f99f6b7084f7f67efab7061.jpg', 'Leo ', 'Rise and shine, says Ganesha, as today will be a sunny day. You will start the day on a very positive note filled with unwavering optimism. Look forward to expressing your views clearly. In fact, the honest opinions you will give at official meetings may push you into the limelight. Remember, compromise without hurting your own dignity. Ganesha expects your soul mate to keep you ‘busy\' in the evening.                  ', '0', '2018-04-20', '2018-04-20 12:04:57', 'Active'),
(41, 23, 11, 47, 23, '7e742abfe0635c16e6ef80dd9203580a.png', 'Vigro', 'You are likely to be the goose mother today - violently protective and intensely reclusive. Intense affairs of the heart will materialise amazingly faster than transporter beams from Star Trek do. Procrastination will finally be slain as Ganesha sees an eventful day in store.                  ', '0', '2018-04-20', '2018-04-20 12:04:36', 'Active'),
(42, 23, 11, 53, 23, '1146a9a3dc5c2d8294ddd404cf5da72f.png', 'Libra', 'Today promises to be an action-packed day for you at work. So, get ready to take the bull by its horns, says Ganesha. Expect to handle a lot of unknown people and unfamiliar situations at work. Evening might find you making a few trips to the market to buy some provisions. Also, love is in the air, and you are in demand. So, the opposite sex will be queuing up to catch a glimpse of you.                  ', '1', '2018-04-20', '2022-04-09 13:02:37', 'Active'),
(43, 23, 11, 48, 23, '476a5e9be713070f4c33e2530eea75bf.jpg', 'scorpio', 'Business will keep you on your toes and make you dance around, says Ganesha. Success is likely to intoxicate you. Ganesha advises you not to let emotions influence your plans and strategies in any way.                  ', '1', '2018-04-20', '2022-01-04 12:45:58', 'Active'),
(44, 23, 11, 49, 23, 'cbafe986341603b3ab68de54b112e41e.jpg', 'Sagittarius ', 'Find yourself taking up the Thinker\'s ponderous posture. Post noon, you may find yourself making plans to rearrange the interior of your home. In the office, your superiors will know your worth and heap appreciation on you, says Ganesha.                  ', '3', '2018-04-20', '2020-01-31 12:43:52', 'Active'),
