(46, 23, 11, 51, 23, '11e1dd9932ccdaf48eb47ea44d18ec3e.png', 'Aquarius ', 'Your ideas may be excellent, says Ganesha, but it\'s your diplomacy and charm which will oil the wheels. You are a silver-tongued smoothie, and can even talk people into eating soap! Family and friends will revel in your company. If you are a student, you may get As in all your tests!                  ', '1', '2018-04-20', '2020-01-31 13:45:15', 'Active'),
(47, 23, 11, 52, 23, 'c61297bf9abf4a94f57913a641410fb6.png', 'Pisces ', 'Your energy levels will be at their peak today, and that, coupled with your extraordinary enthusiasm, will give you the momentum you need to implement your plans, says Ganesha.                                                ', '0', '2018-04-20', '2018-04-20 12:03:22', 'Active'),
(48, 20, 6, 54, 28, 'a74ce9c3592fcf725271f7b90b2dffd4.jpeg', 'Soumyajit Ghosh dropped from Commonwealth Games sq', 'Soumyajit Ghosh has been dropped from India\'s table tennis squad for 2018 Commonwealth Games and placed under provisional suspension, a day after an 18 year old woman levelled allegations of rape against the paddler.\r\n-\r\n\"The Executive Board (EB) of the Table Tennis Federation of India has placed Soumyajit Ghosh under provisional suspension, pending final outcome of the police investigation and court verdict, if any, on the alleged rape charges against him by a teenager,\" TTFI said in a statement.\r\n-\r\n\"During the suspension, he will not be able to participate in any tournament, national or international.\"\r\n-\r\nA complaint has been lodged at the Barasat women\'s police station in North 24 Parganas district in West Bengal, where the 24-year-old Arjuna awardee has been booked under the IPC sections for rape, criminal conspiracy, causing miscarriage without the woman\'s consent and cheating, the police said.\r\n-\r\nThe EB, based on the legal opinion sought by TTFI, discussed the matter with its members earlier in the day.\r\n-\r\n\"The Executive Board of the TTFI, taking cognizance of the media reports and the FIR filed against Soumyajit Ghosh, has unanimously decided to suspend the player and restrain him from participation in all tournaments until further orders,\" TTFI said.\r\n-\r\n\"During its deliberations, the EB took notice of the IPC sections (376, 417, 513, 120(B) and Section 4 of the POCSO Act) under which the Barasat Police (WB) has charged Ghosh.\r\n-\r\n\"Accordingly, the EB members felt that the charges levelled against Ghosh are of grievous nature and they warranted placing him under provisional suspension immediately. EB suggested to TTFI that the player and all authorities concerned should be informed forthwith of the decision.\"\r\n-\r\nTTFI also decided \"to issue a show cause notice to Ghosh, asking him to explain his stand on the FIR lodged by the girl, especially on the allegations against him.\r\n-\r\nThe other members of India\'s table tennis squad are G Sathiyan , A Sharath Kamal, Anthony Amalraj and Harmeet Desai.\r\n-\r\nThe Indian Olympic Association president Narinder Batra on Thursday had said that in case TTFI drops Ghosh, the CWG federation won\'t allow any replacement.\r\n-\r\n\"The matter has not reached the IOA yet but as far as I know, the rule states that a replacement would only be allowed if a particular player sustains injury or falls ill,\" Batra said.\r\n-\r\nIn an exclusive conversation with IndiaToday.in on Thursday, Ghosh accepted that the girl in question was his girlfriend and they dated after meeting each other on Facebook around March 2015. He said that both their families were involved into their relationship and they were supposed to get married but it was the girl who started harassing him mentally.\r\n-\r\n\"It\'s a fake allegation (rape). Actually we met a few years ago on Facebook, around March 2015 and we were together for quite some time, our families knew about it and we were supposed to get married. In fact, when I went to received the Arjuna Award (in 2016), she and her mom were with me then. Suddenly she started opposing my career and travelling and it started to fall apart.\r\n-\r\n Then, she was blackmailing me, forcing and mentally torturing me with threats and all.\r\n-\r\n\"When I went to Europe, she started to show her real character and then I broke up with her because I felt it was too much and I could not play while being with her. I spoke to my family about this also and they supported my decision. This is how it all started,\" Ghosh said\r\n-\r\nGhosh claimed that the girl and her family had been blackmailing him and he has all the evidence to prove his innocence.\r\n\r\n\"For the last one a half years, she and her family have been threatening and blackmailing me through E-mails, chats and non-stop phone calls and what she has done now, she threatened me a year ago. I have all the evidence.\"\r\n-\r\nGhosh added that this may be a plan of the girl and her family to jeopardise his career as the allegations have come just a week before he is set to leave for Australia to participate in the CWG.\r\n-\r\n\"I think this is her or her family\'s plan as just after one week, I am leaving for CWG which is one of the most important things for me right now because I have been preparing for this for the past four years. She wanted to cause this kind of mental harassment so I cannot play well. Right now I am in Germany for the last phase of the CWG preparations so it\'s not easy for me, I have a doubles match today.\r\n-\r\n When we are playing for our nation, it\'s such a proud feeling for us and there\'s so much responsibility on our shoulders that we always want to do better and give our best. I want to play for my country so I will see what I can do.\r\n-\r\n\"I will come back to India because we have to give the dope test before all tournaments and I have to collect my kit also.\"\r\n-\r\nGhosh further alleged that the family has also taken money from him by threatening him. He said he had spoken with a few lawyers because he wanted to take an official action but they mellowed down with the harassment only to suddenly drop these allegations.\r\n-\r\n\"They took some money from me also by threatening me. They also asked for money on loan but never returned that to me. I have all evidence of the money transfers. When her father was in hospital, I paid the bills because they said they had no money and asked me if I could pay. I have helped them in all situations and still I am getting this. \r\n-\r\nI have paid all the money through my credit card because I don\'t use cash much so I have paid through bank transfers and I have proofs of all that.\r\n-\r\nI spoke to two or three lawyers about this because I wanted to take official steps but they asked me to wait and watch. The disturbances began to decrease so my lawyers said it\'s working but then suddenly she has come up with this big thing,\" Ghosh concluded.\r\n\r\n(With PTI inputs)\r\n\r\n                                                      ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(49, 20, 1, 34, 28, 'b959583bf72831ab1a39d7e45f83f120.jpeg', 'Air Asia shows how not to treat passengers at Kolk', 'Around 90 passengers, including senior citizens and children, were made unwitting participants Friday in a airline carrier\'s masterclass on how not to treat clients, delivered at Kolkata airport.\r\n*\r\nHere\'s what happened.\r\n\r\nFirst, an Air Asia flight (Air Asia i5 545) travelling to Ranchi from Delhi was diverted to Kolkata due to to air traffic congestion, and because it didn\'t have enough fuel to keep hovering over the Jharkhand capital.\r\n*\r\nThe plane landed in Kolkata at 2.15 pm. Some of the Ranchi-bound passengers were going to fly onwards to the West Bengal capital anyway, so they de-boarded the plane.\r\n*\r\nThe passengers who needed to get to Ranchi were asked to remain in the aircraft, and did so for an hour. They weren\'t provided food or water.\r\n*\r\nThat was just the beginning of their ordeal.\r\n\r\nWhen they got into an argument with flight attendants, they were asked to de-board the plane. They were told they would be moved to another plane.\r\n*\r\n40 MINUTES IN BUSES\r\n\r\nThe passengers were packed into aerobuses to wait while the second plane was prepared for takeoff.\r\n*\r\nThey remained in the vehicles for 40 to 45 minutes, and were moved out of them when they started feeling suffocated.                                    ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(50, 20, 1, 34, 28, '4c6d3f024b2535df8ffd38314d606167.jpeg', 'Delhi Congress Chief and former Union Minister Aja', 'The Aam Adami Party MLAs\' disqualification again, the Congress termed it a momentary relief.\r\n*\r\nDelhi Congress Chief and former Union Minister Ajay Maken said, all the MLAs accused of office of profit by holding posts of Parliamentary secretaries will loose their Assembly seats as the court has only given them time and not delivered a judgement in their favour.\r\n*\r\n\"The court has not set aside President\'s approval of disqualification, it has only asked the EC to hear the case again for natural justice. This has not been done on merit,\" Maken said.\r\n*\r\nHe said the Congress is also a party in the case and it will stand against the AAP MLAs during hearings in EC.\r\n*\r\n\"I feel they have just got some more time and nothing else. They will he disqualified as soon as the hearing starts,\" said Maken.\r\n*\r\n\"We are gearing up for elections as we know that very soon there will be by elections on these 20 seats and we are hopeful of a grand victory,\" Maken said.\r\n*\r\nTwenty MLAs of the Aam Adami Party were accused of office of profit as they held the positions of parliamentary secretaries.\r\n*\r\nThe party claimed that the MLAs were not paid of this but the EC disqualified them citing their powers and usage of office and public money in construction of such offices.                                                                        ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(52, 22, 16, 65, 30, 'd7b6ff6682443af84027ac7e1b3498e4.png', 'Egyptian Foreign Minister Sameh Shoukry', 'Egypt respects India\'s ability to be a regional and an international player and advocates dialogue between New Delhi and Islamabad over the Kashmir imbroglio. \r\n*\r\nIn an exclusive interview with India Today Group Editorial Director (publishing) Raj Chengappa, Egyptian Foreign Minister Sameh Shoukry said that India and Egypt have been advocates of a rule-based world order and must immunise themselves against any form of terrorism.\r\n*\r\nFrom 1955, when Egypt under Gamal Abdel Nasser and India under Prime Minister Jawaharlal Nehru co-founded the Non-Aligned Movement, to 2018, ties between Cairo and New Delhi have come a long way. Egypt looks to cement its trade, political and economic ties with India further.\r\n*\r\nEgyptian Foreign Minister Sameh Shoukry, who is in India for the seventh session of the Egypt-India joint committee on bilateral relations, said that it is high time for full revival of this strategic relationship. How does Egypt view India\'s role as an international player, especially in the Mideast and Africa? \"India has demonstrated its ability and capability to be both a regional and an international player.\r\n\r\n  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(53, 22, 16, 64, 29, '684f7f830ed5aec77bbb4875cabea8ba.jpeg', 'Centre to offer Taj Mahal and other Agra monuments', 'fter many failed attempts to improve the mismanagement around Taj Mahal, Agra Fort and Fatehpur Sikri, the Union Tourism Ministry has finally decided to offer these monuments up for adoption to any willing private enterprise.\r\n*\r\nIn a meeting called by the Union Tourism Secretary Rashmi Verma in Agra, it was decided that the ministry will offer city monuments for adoption under its \'Adopt Heritage\' plan, wherein private agencies or companies will undertake the maintenance and tourist facilitation.\r\n*\r\nAccording to a senior official, several companies have expressed interest in adopting the Taj Mahal, but there have been no takers for the Agra Fort or Fatehpur Sikri.\r\n*\r\nHe said that the tourism secretary had come to Agra to hold a meeting on \'Iconic Tourist Site Development Project\' and indicated that the Union government was already working on this project and private enterprises have expressed interest in adopting over 60 major monuments in the country.\r\n*\r\nIf this project goes through, the ASI\'s role of maintaining these monuments will be limited to just conservation. Everything from drinking water, parking, landscaping and facilitation will be handed over to the concerned private company.\r\n*\r\nSources from the UP Tourism Department claimed that the project has already been initialised. This meeting was purportedly held to gauge the reactions of the local tourism industry towards the project. Luckily, it did not have any effect on the overall outcome of the project and it was still very much in place.                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(54, 22, 16, 62, 28, '84b4f3858e8db00616f74093b87ab98c.jpeg', 'JNU students clash with cops during rally demandin', 'large number of JNU students and teachers held a protest near INA Market demanding the suspension of Professor Atul Johri who is accused of sexually harassing several students.\r\n*\r\nIrate students clashed with police personnel at the spot. The situation was soon brought under control.\r\n*\r\nJohri, who was arrested on Tuesday, was later released on bail. The arrest was made after incessant protests by various student bodies after cases of sexual harassment came to light.\r\n*\r\nAt the INA Market area, students resorted to sloganeering. The police deployed at the spot fired water cannons to quell the unrest.\r\n*\r\nThe students and teachers held a march from the university campus to Parliament to register their protest against privatisation of education and demanding suspension of Johri.\r\n*\r\nLast week, the police had filed eight FIRs against Johri after teachers held a protest demanding separate FIRs in cases of sexual harassment.\r\n*\r\nThe professor refuted the allegations saying that he was a victim of politics. However, the bail caused resentment among students and teachers who are demanding suspension of Johri.\r\n*\r\nThe students submitted a letter, expressing their displeasure at the bail, and demanding the suspension of Johri, to the university authorities.\r\n*\r\n\"As per JNU Act 20 (1), the Vice-Chanceller of JNU can suspend any faculty on the basis of any allegation of misconduct. We demand that Atul Johri should be immediately suspended given the gravity of the matter,\" read the letter.\r\n*\r\n\"Also, after bail, he can enter the campus anytime. The complainants are registered students of this university and they are in a vulnerable position. We also demand that the administration should declare him out of bounds so that he cannot put any further pressure on the complainants,\" added the letter.                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(55, 22, 16, 65, 26, 'a839dae016b366de441247f9dcf09102.jpeg', '2 killed in hostage-taking at supermarket in Franc', 'Two people were killed when a gunman screaming \"Allahu Akbar\" shot at police and took hostages in a supermarket in southwestern France on Friday.\r\n*\r\nThe French government has confirmed that the attacker has been killed.\r\n*\r\nA source at the Interior Ministry said two had died. \"It is a temporary assessment as it could unfortunately get worse. Three people are wounded, including one of them seriously,\" the source said.\r\n*\r\nEric Menassi, the mayor of the town of Trebes, told BFM TV that the hostage-taker was now alone with one police officer in the supermarket and all other hostages were free.\r\n*\r\nThe station reported that the hostage-taker has claimed allegiance to Islamic State and that he has demanded the release of Salah Abdeslam - the prime surviving suspect in the Islamic State attacks that killed 130 people in Paris in 2015.                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(56, 22, 16, 60, 28, 'd90148d30ee1da3fbd70297769e48f51.png', 'Tamil Nadu farmers get Rs 3, Rs 4, Rs 5 as crop in', 'Rs 3, Rs 4, Rs 5 and Rs 10 as crop insurance. The issue was highlighted when Leader of the Opposition in the Legislative Assembly M K Stalin raised the issue on Wednesday wherein he alleged that farmers had received crop insurance cheques for as little as Rs 3, Rs 4, Rs 5 and Rs 10 in many parts of the state.\r\n*\r\nDMK MLA K Pitchandi even brought a few such cheques to the House. He had questioned in the assembly what was the use of these cheques when a farmer would need a minimum of Rs 500 to open a bank account if he wants to encash these cheques.\r\n*\r\nPitchandi said, \"Farmers are put through lot of hardships. This govt does not care for the welfare of farmers. They have to pay Rs 500 for opening a bank account to encash cheque of Rs 3, 18 etc. This govt has failed to waive off farm loans as well.\r\n* There are so many people who loot tax payers money and escape from our country. The govt has done nothing for farmers interest. That is why I wanted to highlight this issue.\"\r\n*\r\nMeanwhile, senior leaders of the AIADMK have called this clerical mistake. Textile Minister O S Manian is reported to have said that the shortage of staffs was the reason for this mistake and it was purely a clerical mistake.                  ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(57, 20, 10, 18, 28, '0580643903a3b2bef88be396646899ae.jpeg', 'Kate Middleton made her last official outing with Prince William, before her del', 'while the British Royals are looking forward to welcoming another baby into the world, the world has been gushing over Kate Middleton\'s stunning maternity looks--something the Duchess is known for.\r\n*\r\nThe Duchess, who made some really impressive public appearances when she was pregnant with Prince George in 2013 and Princess Charlotte in 2015, seems to have continued with the tradition during her third pregnancy.\r\n*\r\nThe British Royal, who has looked every bit stylish and elegant all this time, made her last official engagement recently, clad in a rather comfortable outfit, which is so unlike her.\r\n*\r\nThe Duchess, who is due in April, ditched her signature vibrant, coat dresses for the event, and put on a pair of skinny, black jeans, leaving almost everyone stunned--because it\'s not every day that the Duchess steps out in a pair of jeans.\r\n*\r\nKnown for her surreal choice of dresses, Kate looked equally refreshing in jeans, which she paired with a printed, black-white top by Hobbs, and looked really chic.\r\n*\r\nThe Duchess, despite her choice of such laidback clothes, looked stunning, as she finished the look with a pair of pearl, drop-down earrings, and black pumps.\r\n*\r\nLooking radiant as ever, the pregnant Duchess made her last official engagement before childbirth, memorable and easy.                                                                        ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(58, 20, 10, 18, 28, '10fe8750641816c2106167b14140556d.jpeg', 'Shilpa Shetty in a Manish Malhotra creation.', 'she can\'t help but admire the bundle of talent that Shilpa Shetty is. Add to that her passion for fitness and health, and one can simply fall in love with this diva. *\r\nWhile there is so much to appreciate about the actress, who is currently a judge on a television reality show, her sense of style isn\'t one of those things.\r\n*\r\nAnyone who is a follower of celebrity-fashion in the country would know of Shilpa\'s love for experimental attires, and how disastrous her looks have been in the past.\r\n*\r\n From pant-suits to sarees, Shilpa has tried her hand at almost all types of fusion-attires, and has had more fashion misses than hits. Adding yet another outfit to her list of fashion fails, Shilpa showed up in a saree-gown, and left us really disappointed.\r\n*\r\nWhile we absolutely love the grand choice of maroon colour for the hybrid ensemble, which did get the temperatures soaring with its corset, sheer blouse, it was the draping that let us down.\r\n*\r\nThe shimmery pallu of the saree-gown by Manish Malhotra looked a bit over-the-top, especially when pinned on the sultry blouse, and robbed the outfit of its elegance.\r\n*\r\nEven the bling and flare towards the hemline looked rather shoddy, just like the misplaced thigh-high slit, which was on the extreme corner of the thigh, thereby defeating the purpose of thigh-high slits.\r\n*\r\nWe liked how she opted for a pair of basic, cream-hued, strappy stilettos without embellishments, which did elevate the look little with its elegance.                                                      ', '0', '2018-03-24', '2018-03-28 13:36:25', 'Active'),
(59, 17, 1, 34, 28, 'd7f3c185db86dc6bb3287c4e34c43637.png', 'Facebook data leak', 'Within days after the row over alleged collusion between Indian political parties and British data-mining firm Cambridge Analytica, the Ministry of Electronics and IT recently issued a notice to the firm seeking details on the breach of data from Facebook.\r\n*\r\nAccording to the notice, the ministry is seeking information based on media reports about questionable practices attributed to the data-mining firm.\r\n*\r\nThe notice, issued on March 23, stated that there was a need for further information about the data breach from Facebook. Accordingly a letter was issued by the ministry today to Facebook seeking their response to a certain set of questions.\r\n*\r\nWhether the personal data of Indian voters and users has been compromised by Cambridge Analytica or any other downstream entity in any manner, and if so, how was it compromised?\r\nWhether Facebook or its related or downstream agencies utilising Facebooks data have previously been engaged by any entities to manipulate the Indian electoral process?\r\nIf any such downstream entity misused data from Facebook, what is the protection available to the data subject?\r\nWhat are the specific steps proposed to be taken by Facebook to prevent any misuse of personal data for potential interference in, or manipulation of the Indian electoral process?\r\n*\r\nFacebook today has its largest footprint in India in terms of its user base and therefore what proactive measures are being taken to ensure the safety, security and privacy of such large user data and to prevent its misuse by any third party?\r\n', '0', '2018-03-28', '2018-03-28 14:02:28', 'Active'),
(60, 17, 1, 34, 28, 'f9b9ffc7761d528080e12e1f549e5a48.jpg', 'ibqsbdw', 'It seems BJP is working hard to clear allegations of murder of 6 protesting farmers in Mandsaur in 2017. The party is giving awards to farmers in every village across Madhya Pradesh.\r\n*\r\nThe awards will be given during the \'Kissan Samman Yatra\', which the party will organize across the state from April 1 to April 15.\r\n*\r\n\"The Kissan Samman Yatra will start from Mathura in Uttar Pradesh on April 1 and reach Mandsaur via Dholpur the same evening. Union Minister Narendra Singh Tomar and state BJP president, Nand Kumar Chouhan will accompany the yatra from Mathura to Morena, where it will culminate in a huge farmers rally,\" MP Kisan Morcha chief Ranvir Singh Rawat said in Bhopal on Wednesday.                  ', '0', '2018-03-28', '2018-04-18 14:16:22', 'Active'),
(61, 17, 1, 35, 28, '07c27d5f479450f6300a42de080dcf23.jpeg', 'At Indus Waters Commission meet', 'India, Pakistan will hold a two-day meeting of the Permanent Indus Commission in New Delhi, starting tomorrow, to discuss various issues under the Indus Waters Treaty (IWT).\r\n*\r\nThe six-member Pakistani delegation will be headed by Syed Muhammad Mehar Ali Shah, while India\'s Indus water commissioner PK Saxena will head the Indian team and will be accompanied by technical experts and a representative of the Ministry of External Affairs (MEA), sources said.\r\n*\r\nThe meeting comes at a time when both countries are facing tremendous strain in ties. This will be the 114th meeting of the Permanent Indus Commission (PIC), which should meet at least once a year as per the Indus Waters Treaty (IWT), sources said.                  \r\n*\r\n\r\nPermanent Indus Commission (PIC) is an established mechanism under the 1960 Indus Waters Treaty between India and Pakistan. The treaty mandates the PIC to establish and maintain cooperative arrangements for the implementation of the treaty and to promote cooperation between the two sides in the development of the Indus water systems.\r\n\r\nEach Commissioner is the representative of his government for all matters arising out of this treaty. The treaty also mandates the PIC to meet at least once a year alternately in India and Pakistan.\r\n\r\nThe last meeting took place in March 2017 in Pakistan. According to the treaty provisions, the 114th meeting of PIC will take place in India on March 29 and March 30 in New Delhi to hold technical deliberations on various issues.\r\n\r\nThe last round of talks related to Indus waters took place in Washington DC in September 2017 on Kishenganga and Ratle hydro electric projects for which the World Bank is the mediating agency but it resulted in no positive outcome as both India and Pakistan stood by their positions.\r\n\r\nAccording to sources, the issues relating to India\'s Ratle, Pakal Dul and Lower Kalnai hydroelectric projects, located in Jammu and Kashmir, may come up for discussion during the meeting.\r\n\r\nPakistan has argued that that Ratle, Pakal Dul and Lower Kalnai projects are violating the Indus Waters Treaty.\r\n\r\nA day ahead of the announcement of the PIC meeting, Union Water Resources Minister Nitin Gadkari categorically said that the Centre is making concerted efforts to stop \"water sharing\" with Pakistan.\r\n*\r\nAddressing the concluding session of Agri Leadership Summit 2018 in Rohtak in Haryana yesterday, Gadkari said, \"During Partition, India got three rivers but we could not utilise our share of the waters, which kept flowing back to Pakistan. Now, the Centre has decided to stop the flow of the country\'s due share into Pakistan and utilise it to feed our parched lands.\"\r\n*\r\nThe Indus Waters Treaty covers water distribution and sharing rights of six rivers--Beas, Ravi, Sutlej, Indus, Chenab and Jhelum. Water from the western rivers are reserved for Pakistan and eastern rivers for India.\r\n\r\nWATCH: Need concrete proof from Pakistan for action against terror: Nirmala Sitharaman\r\n\r\n', '0', '2018-03-28', '2018-03-28 14:06:46', 'Active'),
(62, 22, 4, 23, 28, '2c9812e67c8f89688481e3594c727095.jpeg', 'IDBI Bank discloses fraud of Rs 773 crore', 'crore ($118.8 million) were issued from five of its branches in the states of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana, sending its shares lower on Wednesday.\r\n*\r\nSome of the loans, which were issued during fiscal years 2009-2013 for fish farming businesses, were obtained against fake lease documents of non-existent fish ponds and by inflating the value of collateral, the company said.\r\n*\r\nThe company found major lapses in processing and disbursing the loans by two of its officials. The lender dismissed one of the officials, while the other official had already retired, it said.\r\n*\r\n\r\nIndia\'s federal investigation agency, the Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI), has registered cases for two of the five complaints, relating to branches at Basheerbagh and Guntur, the company said.\r\n\r\nThe bank said earlier on Tuesday it initiated a quality assurance audit, expected to be completed by April.\r\n*\r\nIDBI shares fell as much as 3.5 per cent to 73.6 rupees by 0512 GMT, while the index for public sector lenders Nifty PSU Bank index dropped as much as 1.8 per cent.\r\n', '0', '2018-03-28', '2018-03-28 14:11:14', 'Active'),
(63, 22, 4, 23, 28, 'a7d691f1406b0a656b19eac77f8af95c.jpeg', 'India growth story credible; GDP to grow at 7.3% ', 'The Indian economy is \"credible\" and expected to grow at 7.3 per cent next fiscal driven by private consumption, investment and exports, World Bank said today.\r\n\r\nIn 2019-20, it has projected the growth rate to be higher at 7.5 per cent.\r\n*\r\nFor the current fiscal ending March 31, the Washington-based multi-lateral funding agency has projected the economy to grow at 6.7 per cent.\r\n\r\n\r\nIndia\'s growth has been credible over the long run with growth averaging at 7 per cent in the last decade, it said.\r\n*\r\n\"India\'s GDP growth saw a temporary dip in the last two quarters of 2016-17 and the first quarter of 2017-18 due to demonetisation and disruptions surrounding the initial implementation of GST (Goods and Services Tax),\" World Bank said in its India Development Update.\r\n\r\nThe GDP growth is projected to reach 6.7 per cent in 2017-18 and accelerate to 7.3 per cent and 7.5 per cent in 2018-19 and 2019-20 respectively,\" it said.\r\n\r\nServices will continue to remain the main driver of economic growth, it said.\r\n\r\nIndustrial activity is also poised to grow, with manufacturing expected to accelerate following the implementation of GST, it said, adding that agriculture is likely grow at its long-term average growth rate.\r\n*\r\n\"Steadily and slowly, India has been growing. Its a steady growth, volatility has decreased, the growth is driven by one factor unlike China by exports. India\'s growth is far more diversified through investment, private consumption and exports,\" said Junaid Ahmad, World Bank Country Director in India while talking to reporters in Delhi.', '1', '2018-03-28', '2020-01-31 13:43:58', 'Active'),
(64, 22, 7, 27, 13, 'c1ce0192cc13a0747a09e313c12ddc4f.png', 'Nokia 1 Android Oreo Go Edition at Rs 5,499 may have missed the mark', 'One of the reasons HMD Global had an impressive first run last year with its Nokia branded phones was because not only did it bring out some good-looking smartphone, but more importantly they all came with stock Android software, which not a lot of phones can boast about today. Typically, brands like Xiaomi and Honor, for example, offer up their custom skins that are often heavy and bloated.\r\n*\r\n But HMD was able to offer a stock Android experience with its devices. This year, it takes it a notch higher by going with the Android One program for its phones. Even the Nokia 1, its entry-level offering, comes with Android Oreo Go Edition and was recently launched in India at Rs 5,499.\r\n*\r\nFor those wondering, Google launched the Android Oreo (Go edition) which is essentially an Oreo-based software designed for entry-level smartphones that come with 1GB of RAM or lower. The software comes with its own set of core Google apps such as Google Go, YouTube Go and Gmail Go, among other.\r\n*\r\n It promises to bring the latest and best of Android and makes sure it runs smoothly on phones with bare-boned hardware. The idea behind this is to offer good low-end smartphones for first time users looking to give up their feature phones. In fact, one of the prime targets for Google is India which still sees a huge market of people using feature phones.', '0', '2018-03-28', '2018-03-28 15:11:34', 'Active'),
(65, 20, 1, 34, 29, 'eba494d58881de8ee37c810de163abf2.png', 'India successfully launches GSAT-6A ', 'India today successfully launched the GSAT-6A satellite that would provide mobile communication facilities, using its heavy rocket Geosynchronous Satellite Launch Vehicle (GSLV-F08), in a copy-book style.\r\n*\r\nThe GSLV-MkII rocket slung the satellite in a geosynchronous transfer orbit (GTO) from where it would be taken up to its final geostationary orbit by three orbit raising manoeuvres.\r\n*\r\nISRO\'s scientists at the mission control centre were visibly happy, slapping each others\' backs and hugging each other once the rocket ejected the satellite into the intended orbit.\r\n\r\n*\r\nPrecisely at 4.56 pm, the GSLV rocket ascended into the sky from the second launch pad here at Satish Dhawan Space Centre and the 49.1 metre tall rocket, weighing 415.6 tonne, slung the two tonne satellite into the intended orbit 17.46 minutes into its flight.\r\n\r\nThe purpose of the satellite is to provide mobile communication applications in S-band in five spot beams and C-band in one beam during its 10-year life span.\r\n\r\nThe Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO) said that the GSAT-6A was similar to the GSAT-6 put into orbit in 2015.                  ', '0', '2018-03-29', '2018-03-29 13:32:55', 'Active'),
(66, 20, 10, 12, 23, '42d7f29a76c488432460c9792e8b1f0f.jpeg', 'A workout that keeps you in shape and also saves the planet', 'your body healthy but also your surrounding environment?\r\n\r\nThis unique form of workout is now catching on as a trend among fitness enthusiasts.\r\n\r\nCalled plogging, the eco-friendly workout originated from Sweden, and helps one burn calories while taking care of the planet.\r\n\r\n\r\nPlogging is a combination of jogging and the Swedish term \'\'plocka upp,\'\' meaning \'\'pick up.\'\' This basically means that rather than just jogging past the garbage littered on the streets, ploggers also make sure they pick it up and dispose of it correctly, mentions Independent in an article.\r\n*\r\n\r\nPlogging is said to burn more calories than regular jogging. Since plogging requires bending and arm strength to hold the garbage, 30 mins of plogging can burn 288 calories on an average, as compared to 235 calories burnt during regular jogging.\r\n\r\nSome ploggers also add additional exercises as they bend to pick up garbage, in order to keep their heart rate pumping.', '0', '2018-03-29', '2018-03-29 13:35:29', 'Active'),
(67, 20, 9, 30, 28, 'ba64703481833f5e9cc445e98967b503.png', '44-year-old mother from Ludhiana appears for Class 10 board exam with her son', 'Someone has said it right, that there is no age to complete education and it\'s never too late to go back to school.\r\n\r\nHere is an inspiring story of Rajni Bala, a 44-year-old lady, who is appearing for Class 10 Board Exam 2018 along with her son.\r\n\r\nThis clearly proves that education and attaining knowledge has no age limit.\r\n\r\n\r\nAs reported, Rajni Bala had completed Class 9 in 1989, but due to an unfortunate family circumstance, she had to give up her education. Eventually, she was married and began her family life.\r\n\r\n*\r\nHERE WHAT RAJNI BALA SAID:\r\n\"My husband has been telling me for several years to complete my education. However, I had three children and had to educate them. Although I am working as a ward attendant in a civil hospital, I realised that it is important to pass Class 10 at least, in the present day. Therefore, I began preparing along with my son, who is also in Class 10. We go to school together and study also together,\" Rajni told ANI.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, Pawan Gaur, Principal of Lajwanti Senior Secondary School in Ludhiana, where the mother-son duo are studying, stated that when individuals come back to complete their education after several years, it sends a very positive message to the society at large.', '0', '2018-03-29', '2018-03-29 13:38:12', 'Active'),
(68, 20, 6, 9, 28, '7777432d799331729915a9eb5fd76c32.jpeg', 'Ball-Tampering Scandal: Steve Smith broke down during public apology', 'Steve Smith broke down during a press conference at the Sydney airport upon his return from South Africa.\r\n\r\nSmith took full responsibility for the ball-tampering scandal and said he was deeply sorry for the episode that rocked Australian cricket.\r\n\r\nSmith and David Warner were banned for a year by Cricket Australia. Following CA\'s decision, BCCI barred the duo from playing in the Indian Premier League this year.\r\n\r\n*\r\n\r\nCameron Bancroft, who was caught by TV cameras trying to tamper the ball, was banned for nine months.\r\n\r\nSmith and Bancroft fronted up to the media while Warner issued a statement on his social media platforms.\r\n\r\nSmith has also been banned from leading Australia for a futher 12 months after his return to international cricket. Warner will never be allowed to lead Australia again.\r\n', '0', '2018-03-29', '2018-03-29 13:40:42', 'Active'),
(69, 20, 7, 27, 28, 'a640271628f297b790a9f0e776bdad85.jpeg', 'OnePlus 6 to come with notch, 3.5mm jack', 'nePlus 6 will launch very soon, most likely in the next several weeks or so. OnePlus co-founder Carl Pei on Wednesday confirmed that the new OnePlus phone is coming and with a notch similar to that of the iPhone X because that is the latest trend that most smartphone makers are adapting for their high-end phones.\r\n\r\nPei also confirmed to the Verge that the upcoming OnePlus 6 will have the biggest display compared to all OnePlus phones.\r\n*\r\nMost Android phone makers are adapting the iPhone X notch. The newly launched flagship device by Huawei - P20 Pro and also the P20 comes with iPhone X-like notch. Meanwhile, Vivo\'s latest phones - that is the Vivo V9 has a notch on its display. OnePlus has always been keen towards adapting the ongoing trend. And the company will be following the same for the OnePlus 6 as well. But, OnePlus co-founder Carl Pei said that the notch on the OnePlus 6 will be much better than that of the Android phones from other companies. The OnePlus co-founder didn\'t confirm any further details about the OnePlus 6.\r\n*\r\nThe first image of the OnePlus 6 was leaked on Wednesday by Evan Blass, a popular tipster who\'s often accurate with his predictions. The image shows the OnePlus 6 with a wooden textured back cover, centrally-placed rear cameras, with a fingerprint sensor below the lens. OnePlus will retain the 3.5mm headphone for the device. OnePlus 6 has been subjected to several leaks and rumours so far, let\'s take a quick look at what we know about the device so far.\r\n\r\nOnePlus 6 India launch and expected price\r\n\r\nOnePlus CEO and co-founder Pete Lau earlier confirmed the next OnePlus flagship will launch in Q2 2018. We can most likely expect the OnePlus 6 to launch in May or early June in India, with May looking like a bigger possibility.\r\n\r\nAs for the pricing, OnePlus 6 could be expensive, a bit more expensive than the OnePlus 5T. We say this on the basis OnePlus co-founder Pete Lau\'s tweet back late last year. Lau had posted, \"Cost of smartphone components is rising, but phones are also getting better. OnePlus users will appreciate what\'s coming.\"\r\n', '0', '2018-03-29', '2018-03-29 13:43:34', 'Active');
