(95, 17, 1, 34, 13, '58cc082237fba84ca473066f8d039307.jpg', 'In Mumbai, BJP chief Amit Shah likens opposition to cats, dogs & snakes united a', 'Apart from the Center, the Bharatiya Janata Party, which is in power in many states of the country, is celebrating its 39th Raising Day today. BJP is celebrating its foundation day with loud noise. Party President Amit Shah addressed a major rally in Mumbai on Friday. In the evening, Prime Minister Narendra Modi will communicate directly with the workers of 5 parliamentary constituencies.  \r\n*\r\nAddressing the rally, party president Amit Shah said that in the history of India\'s democracy, BJP workers have given the highest sacrifice. In his speech, Shah described the workers as the real master of the party. 38 years ago when Atalji had established BJP in Mumbai, he had said that darkness will be removed, sun will leave and lotus will be opened. Today lotus has been feeding all over the country.\r\n*\r\nFear of Modi\'s flood in opposition\r\n*\r\nAmit Shah said that when every flood occurs in every forest, every tree falls and the tree remains standing. When a flood comes, the snake-cat catches on the tree to protect themselves. Shah said that the fear of flooding of the snake-necklace-dogs are fighting together and fighting elections. Today, in the leadership of Modi ji, the BJP government has more than 20 states. In 2019, again the BJP will form the government with majority.', '0', '2018-04-06', '2018-04-06 10:34:36', 'Active'),
(96, 20, 1, 35, 28, '6dc3ed70acc44fd7fd6e99b48f098847.png', '$20 billion defence project: India kicks off process to procure 110 fighter jets', 'NEW DELHI: It\'s jet set, go, all over again! India has kicked off a fresh dogfight for its $20 billion \"mother of all defence deals\" by re-inviting global aviation majors to compete for producing fighter jets in India under the government\'s \"strategic partnership\" policy.\r\nIAF on Friday issued a preliminary global tender or RFI (request for information) to acquire 110 fighter jets, of which 85% are to be built in India with a domestic strategic partner or production agency. The aviation majors have to submit their responses to the RFI, which also stipulates that 75% of the fighters will be single-seat jets, by July 3.\r\n*\r\n\"The project will cost an estimated Rs 1.25 lakh crore. IAF hopes to issue the formal tender or RFP (request for proposal), inviting technical and commercial bids, within 6-12 months of getting the responses to the RFI,\" said a top source. \r\n*\r\n\"The project will cost an estimated Rs 1.25 lakh crore. IAF hopes to issue the formal tender or RFP (request for proposal), inviting technical and commercial bids, within 6-12 months of getting the responses to the RFI,\" said a top source.\r\n\r\nThough it’s very early days as yet because the entire process of submission of RFP bids, complex evaluation and field trials will take some years, the aim is to set up a second fighter manufacturing line in India to supplement the long-delayed production of indigenous Tejas jets.\r\n*\r\nIAF, after all, is grappling with just 31 fighter squadrons (each with 18 jets) when at least 42 are required to tackle the \"collusive threat\" from Pakistan and China. Moreover, the 10 existing squadrons of old MiG-21s and MiG-27s are slated for retirement by 2022. ', '0', '2018-04-06', '2018-04-06 15:19:15', 'Active'),
(97, 20, 1, 34, 28, '8322f214c5087571767183dc94aeda12.png', 'Rahul Gandhi at an election rally in Bengaluru.', 'Responding to Rahul Gandhi\'s claim that PM Narendra Modi may lose his Varanasi seat in the Lok Sabha polls of 2019, BJP said that Sonia Gandhi and the Congress chief will lose their respective constituencies of Raebareli and Amethi.\r\n*\r\nThe BJP added that the reason for this was people\'s growing \"disappointment\" with them.\r\nParty spokesperson Anil Baluni said Rahul should be worried about his and his mother\'s electoral fate in 2019 and should not worry about Modi\'s.\r\n\r\n\"In the kind of circumstances prevailing today, both Rahul and his mother, Sonia Gandhi, will lose from their seats, Amethi and Raebareli, respectively. They have done nothing in their constituencies and the people\'s disappointment with them is growing,\" he said.\r\n*\r\nThe comments came in the backdrop of Rahul Gandhi\'s claim that Modi may lose from Varanasi against a united opposition in 2019.\r\n\r\n*\r\nIn the kind of circumstances prevailing today, both Rahul and his mother, Sonia Gandhi, will lose from their seats, Amethi and Raebareli, respectively. They have done nothing in their constituencies and the people\'s disappointment with them is growing,\" he said.\r\n*\r\nThe comments came in the backdrop of Rahul Gandhi\'s claim that Modi may lose from Varanasi against a united opposition in 2019.\r\n\r\nPegging his confidence on opposition unity, Gandhi had said on Sunday that far from the BJP winning the 2019 Lok Sabha polls, even Modi might lose from Varanasi if his party, the SP and the BSP were united against him.\r\n*\r\nExuding confidence over roping in and managing alliance partners despite their varied personal and regional aspirations, Gandhi predicted that the current ruling dispensation would witness a \"collapse\" not \"seen in many years.\"\r\n*\r\n\"Frankly, I don\'t see the BJP winning the next election, so in 2019 we will go back to the normal, I sense,\" he said in reply to a question on \"Dalit anger.\"', '1', '2018-04-11', '2018-04-18 13:15:30', 'Active'),
(98, 20, 6, 68, 34, 'f0db1c17bae1ce41036c8ed5678a2c7d.png', 'Jitu Rai\'s (Centre) medal was India\'s 8th Gold in CWG 2018 so far', 'tar shooter Jitu Rai bagged the second Gold in shooting for India at the Commonwealth Games 2018 with a masterful performance in the Men\'s 10m Air Pistol Final in Gold Coast on Monday.\r\n*\r\nJitu created a new CWG record of 235.1 in the final to win the gold. Kerry Bell of Australia took silver with 233.5 while Om Mitharwal bagged the bronze for India with a score of 214.3.\r\n*\r\nEarlier, Om enjoyed a promising start to his campaign and emerged as the best shooter in the qualification stage. He equalled the Commonwealth Games (CWG) record on his way to qualifying for the final.\r\n\r\nOm shot 584 in the qualifying round to equal the record set by fellow Indian Samaresh Jung at the 2006 CWG in Melbourne. Rai reached the final with a score of 570.\r\n\r\nIndia now have 15 medals at the Gold Coast Games with 8 Gold, 3 Silver and 4 Bronze.\r\n\r\n*\r\nMinutes before Rai and Mitharval\'s shooting medals, India had bagged the silver in weightlifting as Pardeep Singh finished second in the Men\'s 105kg Final to clinch the first medal for the country on day 5.', '0', '2018-04-11', '2018-04-11 12:55:39', 'Active'),
(102, 20, 5, 73, 13, 'a9dd54e52939767e13bcf49a41101645.JPG', 'Rising Star 2 winner is Hemant Brijwasi, had won Sa Re Ga Ma Lil Champs earlier.', 'Hemant Brijwasi of Mathura won the top honour in the reality television singing show, Rising Star 2 on Sunday, reports Zoom TV. Garnering 83% votes, he beat Rohanpreet Singh of Punjab and Vishnumaya Ramesh from Kerala to take took home a trophy and prize money of Rs 20 lakhs. Brijwasi had won another reality show, Sa Re Ga Ma Lil Champs earlier.\r\n*\r\nA tough three-month battle saw Hemant, Rohanpreet, Vishnumaya and Zaid Ali match their talent in a show that was judged by composer Shankar Mahadevan, singer-actor Monali Thakur and Punjabi singer-actor Diljit Dosanjh.\r\n*\r\nThe quartet competed till the end, before the elimination of Zaid Ali. At one point, Rohanpreet and Vishnumaya were tied at 78%. However, the boy from Punjab edged out his competitor from Kerala in a stiff competition.\r\n\r\nWhile Rohanpreet impressed all with his rendition of Khuda Jaane from Bachna Ae Haseeno, Vishnumaya sang Silsila Ye Chaahat Ka from Devdas. Finally, it was left to Hemant to mesmerise his audience with Alvida from Life in a Metro and win the title, reports BollywoodLife.\r\n*\r\nIt may be recalled here that Hemant is not new to winning laurels for his talent. Nine years ago, Hemant won the Sa Re Ga Ma Pa Li’l Champs in 2009, a Zoom report says. He was a participant in India’s Got Talent in 2016 and Jo Jeeta Wohi Superstar 2 as well.', '9', '2018-04-16', '2020-08-01 06:38:59', 'Active'),
(106, 20, 5, 10, 13, '3cc5812b831c8ea7a3b185d750754187.jpeg', 'Baaghi 2 total collection: Tiger Shroff and Disha Patani film races past Rs 150 ', 'Tiger Shroff and Disha Patani are on cloud nine. Their first film together, Baaghi 2, is shattering records at the box office and how!\r\n\r\nThe film hit the screens on March 30 this year and it has now crossed the Rs 150-crore mark at the box office in India.\r\n\r\nIn two weeks at the screens, Baaghi 2 has earned Rs 155.65 crore. The film is a sequel to 2016\'s Baaghi, that also starred Tiger Shroff in the lead role. Shraddha Kapoor played Tiger\'s love interest in the first film.\r\n\r\nDirected by Ahmed Khan, Baaghi 2 received largely lukewarm to negative reviews. The slick action sequences in the film, however, were appreciated.\r\n*\r\nBaaghi 2 is the official remake of Telugu mystery thriller Kshanam that released in 2016.\r\n\r\nTiger Shroff plays Ronny, an Indian Army officer who takes a break to help his ex-girlfriend Neha (Disha Patani) when her daughter goes missing.\r\n\r\nBaaghi 2 opened to fabulous numbers at the box office. In its first week itself, the film crossed the Rs 100-crore mark in India.\r\n\r\nAfter raking in Rs 112.85 crore in the first week, Baaghi 2 went on to collect Rs 35.6 crore in the next seven days.\r\n\r\nThe film has been performing well at single-screen theatres.\r\n\r\nApart from Tiger and Disha in the lead roles, Bagahi 2 stars Manoj Bajpayee, Prateik Babbar and Randeep Hooda.', '2', '2018-04-16', '2018-04-19 13:40:38', 'Active'),
(107, 20, 5, 10, 13, 'e4132aa58bfa337be4bb797046d0bcee.jpg', 'abc', 'abcd', '2', '2018-04-16', '2022-04-09 13:01:10', 'Active'),
(108, 22, 10, 22, 28, 'b5fac594e62b2cf7414da8fee84fd377.jpg', 'Before you plan your holiday, do a thorough research of the agency you are tying', 'Adventure sports are unique in their adrenaline-inducing capabilities, owing to the thrill and ‘risque’ factor involved. However, a sports lover must venture into such extreme activities after being educated into the art of taking a ‘calculated risk, say experts.\r\n\r\nNiharika Nigam, business development director at Jumpin Heights, lists some precautionary measures that need to be kept in mind:\r\n\r\n* Research on your destination and associated safety measures: The success and failure of this industry comes down to one primary aspect and that is safety. One should do some primary research on the company providing their chosen activity before visiting, look up testimonials, ratings and should take appropriate measures. Ask questions about the safety practices followed, understand how disciplined is the organisation in the maintenance of the same.\r\n\r\nPack wisely and smartly for the trip: While going on for an adventure trip, one must pack efficiently and smartly. They should carry all the necessary trip accessories like water bottle, flashlight or torch, portable charger, sunglasses, sleeping bag sheet, medicines and some toiletries in their backpacks. \r\nLoosen up: The whole point of adventure sports is to expand our horizon, shatter the glass ceiling we set for ourselves and step out of our comfort zones. Acknowledging this larger picture pushes one to truly embrace the experience and squeeze out every ounce of benefit and glory from that one exhilarating opportunity.\r\n*\r\nPushpendra Sharma, founder of HotelDekho.com, suggests:\r\n\r\nThe fitness challenge: Understanding your fitness levels is important to get the maximum out of your adventure. Do not put your health at risk by trying something that you are clearly not capable of. Ensure you have got your medical tests done and consulted your doctor before attempting something you have never done before. The tests may vary depending on the nature of the activity you are planning to indulge in.\r\n*\r\nGet insured: Buy a travel insurance plan that will safeguard you and your loved ones in case of any unforeseen incidents during your adventure trip. Before buying a policy go through the details and consult an expert to see if the plans will cover the mishaps that could result from the sport you are going to attempt. There are many insurance options, however, choosing a suitable one is always a challenge.', '20', '2018-04-16', '2022-04-05 12:59:49', 'Active'),
(109, 22, 15, 8, 28, '48c5de1f2f411f6cd108272484543bc7.jpeg', 'Karnataka opinion poll: Where do voters stand on issues of Kannada language, sep', 'Going into Assembly polls next month, Karnataka\'s politics has been dominated by several controversial issues in the recent past. The India Today-Karvy opinion polls tried to gauge voter\'s view on these issues made headlines and sparked controversies.\r\n\r\nResponding to a question on the Karnataka government\'s decision to make Kannada language mandatory for all schools, 73 per cent of the respondents said that they supported the move. Only 16 per cent opposed the Siddaramaiah government\'s decision while 10 per cent had no opinion on the question.\r\n*\r\nSimilarly on the question of Karnataka having its own flag, six of ten voters supported the Siddaramaiah government. About 59 per cent voters said that they were with the government on the issue while 29 per cent opposed the move. Rest 12 per cent remained non-committal.\r\n\r\nOn the question of celebrating Tipu Sultan\'s birth anniversary, which became a major flashpoint between the Siddaramaiah government and the BJP, the people\'s opinion was divided. Only 32 per cent supported the Congress government\'s move to celebrate Tipu Jayanti while 44 per cent opposed the decision. However, 58 per cent Muslim voters favoured celebrating Tipu Sultan\'s birth anniversary.\r\n*\r\nOn another controversial matter of the decision of the state government to recommend to the Centre to recognise Lingayat community as a separate religious denomination, 52 per cent voters said that it would be a major issue for the upcoming Karnataka election.', '16', '2018-04-16', '2020-01-01 14:45:25', 'Active'),
(110, 20, 6, 11, 28, 'edd9b3ad005560da24048905926403ec.png', 'After Manchester City win Premier League, Jose Mourinho lashes out at United.', 'Manchester United fell to a 1-0 defeat at Old Trafford against relegation-threatened West Bromwich Albion on Sunday to hand over the Premier League title to their city rivals.\r\n\r\nJust a week ago, United had put up an inspired performance at the Etihad Stadium, where they came from two goals down to beat City 3-2, and prevented Manchester City\'s perfect title scoop.\r\n*\r\nHowever, on Sunday, United looked lazy and uninspired and one mistake during the match cost them a humiliating defeat against the bottom-placed West Brom.\r\n*\r\nThe loss handed City the title, leaving United trailing by 16 points with five games remaining, and Mourinho immediately faced the question of whether he was confident his team could make a real challenge next year.\r\n\r\n\"I trust in my work, that is for sure, I have no reason not to trust. Eight titles are eight titles and three Premier Leagues are three Premier Leagues,\" he said.\r\n*\r\n\"I trust in my work, that is for sure, I have no reason not to trust. Eight titles are eight titles and three Premier Leagues are three Premier Leagues,\" he said.\r\n\r\n\"The last title was not 20 years ago it was three years ago. I know how to win, I believe in myself but I don\'t play,\" added the former Chelsea and Real Madrid manager. ', '0', '2018-04-16', '2018-04-16 10:40:57', 'Active'),
(111, 20, 6, 9, 28, 'f06dd634a8e1f9ee4dd9513a49c88347.png', 'MS Dhoni kept everyone on the edge of their seat: Virender Sehwag', 'MS Dhoni took people back in time on Sunday smashing a career-best T20 score of 79 not out from 44 balls even as Chennai Super Kings lost to Kings XI Punjab by four runs in the Indian Premier League in Mohali.\r\n\r\nEven with a bad back, when he was struggling to run at his normal pace between the wickets, Dhoni almost got his team home hitting 6 fours and 5 sixes.\r\n*\r\nThere was a sense of nostalgia about the match with Dhoni showing his explosive power again, hitting a six off the final ball but alas! Chennai still fell short.\r\n\r\nWith Dhoni putting up a show of the skills he is known for, Twitter did not hold back from showering praises on one of India\'s greatest finishers.\r\n*\r\nVirender Sehwag congratulated his team (KXIP) on winning the match but praised Dhoni for his \"excellent knock.\"\r\n\r\nSanjay Manjrekar also said that despite CSK\'s loss, Dhoni\'s \"unbelievable knock\" made him the winner on Sunday.', '2', '2018-04-16', '2022-02-11 15:11:03', 'Active'),
(112, 20, 10, 18, 13, '55d714451500641f10232b66e4012ba8.png', 'Manushi Chillar in this feminine pant-suit is making power-dressing look so easy', 'Ever since Manushi Chhillar has been crowned Miss World 2017, the 20-year-old\'s name has become synonymous to style.\r\n\r\nFrom serene sarees to floral dresses, Manushi had started channelising her inner fashionista while she was still competing for the coveted crown, and she has only grown better with time.\r\n*\r\nWhile we were still trying to get over her surreal lehenga choices, the beauty queen decided to make sure we swoon over her idea of power-dressing too.\r\n\r\nThe last time Manushi made an attempt to embrace the idea of power-dressing, her velvet pant-suit had let us down, and there couldn\'t have been a better way of redemption than her recent look.\r\n*\r\nClad in a white pant-suit by Gaurav Gupta, which was just the right blend of feminine and powerful, thanks to the flamboyant floral motifs all over, Manushi looked like a sight to behold.\r\n\r\nApart from being florid, the floral motifs were a total winner because of the subtle choice of pistachio colour, which lent elegance to the heavy work.\r\n*\r\nWhile the colours and motifs were really chic, adding a rather trendy and vintage-y touch to the look were the trumpet, sheer sleeves. The clever choice of the fabric was a genius move, considering how suffocating and over-the-top the sleeves would have looked otherwise.\r\n\r\nWhat\'s more, the flared bottoms were in coherence with the ancient-yet-trendy looking trumpet sleeves, and made the ensemble look like a masterpiece from the \'70s.\r\n\r\nSticking to her signature hairdo--straight hair left loose--the beauty queen wore minimal makeup, and looked ready to rule, while being every bit pretty.\r\n', '3', '2018-04-16', '2018-04-19 06:17:38', 'Active'),
(113, 20, 7, 27, 28, 'a2144f8ed1de3c31298f0868829aefda.jpeg', 'Xiaomi Black Shark gaming smartphone launched', 'Xiaomi backed subsidiary Black Shark has launched its high-end gaming phone in China. The phone in question, does not have a dedicated name per se and is called simply the Black Shark. The Black Shark, which seems to be Xiaomi\'s take on the Razer phone, comes with some high-end specs and some that have been exclusively packed in for gamers.\r\n\r\nThe Black Shark gaming phone, is however, not as big and boxy as the Razer phone which means it would find takers even among other buyers. That said, it\'s highly unlikely, that it would ever make its way outside of China anytime soon. Here\'s a closer look at the newly launched Xiaomi Black Shark gaming smartphone.\r\n*\r\nSpecifications:\r\n\r\nProcessor: The Black Shark is powered by a 2.8GHz octa-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 845 processor clubbed with Adreno 630 GPU.\r\n\r\nRAM: The Black Shark will be available in two RAM versions: 6GB and 8GB.\r\n\r\nInternal storage: While the 6GB RAM version of the Black Shark will be available with 64GB storage, the top-end 8GB RAM version will come with 128GB storage. The Black Shark does not support expandable storage.\r\n*\r\nScreen: The Black Shark comes with a 5.99-inch Full-HD+ 18:9 display with a 2160x1080 pixel resolution and 403ppi pixel density. It supports the DCI-P3 wide colour gamut standard.\r\nRear camera: The Black Shark comes with a dual camera system on the rear consisting of one 12-megapixel sensor and another 20-megapixel sensor. Both have an f/1.75 aperture. The dual camera system is further assisted by a dual-LED flash.\r\n\r\nFront camera: On the front, the Black Shark comes with a 20-megapixel camera.\r\n\r\nSoftware: The Black Shark runs Android Oreo-based Joy UI.\r\n*\r\nBattery: The Black Shark is backed by a 4,000mAah battery and supports Qualcomm\'s Quick Charge 3.0 charging. The phone charges over USB Type-C port.\r\n\r\nSpecial features:\r\n\r\n-- The Black Shark gaming phone comes with liquid cooling, that can help users -- gamers -- keep temperature down while intensive gaming. It can apparently help reduce the CPU\'s core temperature by up to 8-degrees.\r\n\r\n-- Also the Black Shark comes with a dedicated Shark key that when enabled devotes all hardware resources to your game for more immersive gaming.\r\n*\r\n-- The Black Shark comes with dual Biso stereo speakers. The phone, however does not have a headphone jack.\r\n\r\n-- In addition to the Snapdragon 845, the Black Shark gaming phone also packs in a dedicated Pixelworks image processing chip that supports something that the company is calling intelligent motion compensation technology that aids in image enhancement and dark scene detail processing for enhanced gaming experiences.\r\n*\r\n-- In terms of all-round design, the Black Shark has curved sides, and rounded edges, a stark departure from the Razer phone\'s big boxy design. It will be available in two colour options: Polar Night and Sky Gray. The phone comes with a front-mounted fingerprint scanner and a glowing logo on the back.\r\n\r\n-- Xiaomi has also launched a one-sided gamepad along side the Black Shark gaming phone that attaches to the device via Bluetooth. The mod, while acting as a gamepad, also has an internal 340 mAh battery, that is claimed to offer up to 30 hours of gaming on a single charge.\r\n*\r\nPrice and availability\r\n\r\nThe Black Shark gaming phone will start at 2999 yuan (roughly Rs 31,000) for the 6GB RAM and 64GB storage version going all the way to 3499 yuan (roughly Rs 36,000) for the top-end 8GB RAM and 128GB storage version. The gamepad mod will be sold separately for 179 yuan (roughly Rs 2,000). Xiaomi has announced that the first 50,000 buyers will get the gamepad mod for free with the Black Shark. The Black Shark gaming phone will be available for buying in China from April 20.\r\n', '3', '2018-04-16', '2022-02-11 15:10:47', 'Active'),
(114, 20, 7, 27, 28, '06d63dd1f97650811c58f9d66c0da372.jpeg', 'BHIM app offers cashback worth up to Rs 750 to customers, here\'s how to get it.', 'After telecom, the next big war that we are seeing these days is between the e-wallets. The leading e-wallets in the country including government\'s launched BHIM app are neck and neck to earn more users. Taking a cue from its rivals, the government announced a BHIM cashback scheme under which user can receive a cashback of up to Rs 750 every month.\r\n*\r\nBefore you understand how this scheme works and how can you become eligible for the cashback, it is worth knowing that this scheme was launched by Prime Minister Narendra Modi on April 14, 2017, to promote cashless payments through the BHIM app. The scheme was extended till March 31 for the merchants and the monthly limit for merchants under this cashback scheme is up to Rs 1000.\r\nThe government has now announced a cashback worth Rs 750 for the customers. So now customers can earn cashback worth up to Rs 750 while merchants can earn up to Rs 1000.\r\n*\r\nSo how does this cashback scheme work?\r\n\r\nThose who download the BHIM app, link it to their bank account and complete the first financial transaction will receive a cashback of Rs 51. There\'s a cashback of Rs 25 for every unique transaction with a minimum value of Rs 100. The maximum cashback limit for a month is up to Rs 500.\r\n\r\nFor a minimum transaction value of Rs 10 and above, BHIM is offering cashback depending on the number of transactions user makes. For 20 to 50 transactions there\'s a cashback worth Rs 50, Rs 200 for 50-100 transactions and Rs 250 for transactions more than 100.\r\n*\r\nFor merchants receiving payments via BHIM/BHIM UPI app, there\'s a cashback of 10 per cent of the transaction value with a maximum of Rs 50 per transaction. The minimum credit transaction value here is Rs 25 and number of minimum credit transactions is 5.\r\n\r\nLaunched in 2016, BHIM is a mobile app developed by National Payments Corporation of India, based on the Unified Payment Interface.\r\n', '4', '2018-04-16', '2018-04-16 15:03:22', 'Active'),
(115, 20, 16, 60, 28, '26b31609d0c1510d8cab339870d31a83.png', 'India\'s weather office forecasts average monsoon rains in 2018.', 'India is likely to receive average monsoon rains in 2018, the weather office said, raising the possibility of higher farm and economic growth in Asia\'s third-biggest economy, where half of the farmland lacks irrigation.\r\n*\r\nMonsoon rains, the lifeblood of the country\'s $2 trillion economy, are expected to be 97 percent of a long-term average, K.J. Ramesh, director general of the state-run India Meteorological Department (IMD), told a news conference.\r\n*\r\nOther than lifting farm and wider economic growth, a wet spell will keep a lid on inflation, potentially tempting Prime Minister Narendra Modi to bring forward general elections due in May 2019.\r\n*\r\nIndia\'s weather office defines average, or normal, rainfall as between 96 percent and 104 percent of a 50-year average of 89 cms for the entire four-month season beginning June.', '0', '2018-04-16', '2018-04-16 11:03:45', 'Active'),
(116, 20, 16, 60, 28, '80a653baaa10e8565e789d1a4c2be013.jpeg', 'Kathua accused plead not guilty, ask for narco test.', 'The eight people accused of raping and killing an eight-year-old pleaded not guilty and asked the judge for a narco analysis test as the trial into the case, which has become the focal point of outrage across the country, began here today.\r\n\r\nSeven of the eight accused were produced before District and Sessions Judge Sanjay Gupta, who asked the state Crime Branch to give them copies of the chargesheet and fixed April 28 as the next date of hearing.\r\n*\r\nThe eighth accused is a juvenile who moved a bail application before the chief judicial magistrate. The matter was posted for April 26.\r\n\r\nThe child from a minority nomadic community was allegedly held in captivity in a small village temple in Kathua district for a week in January this year during which she was kept, sedated and sexually assaulted before being bludgeoned to death.\r\n*\r\nAccording to the chargesheets filed by the Crime Branch, the abduction, rape and killing of the girl was part of a carefully planned strategy to remove the nomadic community from the area. A separate chargesheet was filed for the juvenile.\r\n\r\nThe counsel for the accused demanded a copy of the chargesheet filed by the Crime Branch on April 9 before the chief judicial magistrate.\r\n\r\nImmediately after the brief hearing in the sessions court, the seven accused were shifted back to the jail under heavy security.\r\n*\r\nSpecial police officer Deepak Khajuria, who is alleged to have repeatedly raped the child told reporters from the police van that he was also demanding a narco test, also known as the \"truth test\", and a CBI probe.\r\n\r\nAs the trial began inside the court, main accused Sanji Ram\'s daughter Madhu Sharma protested outside, demanding a CBI probe.\r\n\r\nThere was heavy police presence at the Kathua complex following the tension on April 9 when members of the local bar association did not allow the Crime Branch to submit its chargesheet in the case.\r\n*\r\nSanji Ram, the caretaker of the devisthan in a village in Kathua, about 90 km from Jammu, is listed as the main conspirator behind the crime.\r\n\r\nHe was allegedly joined by special police officers Deepak Khajuria and Surender Verma, friend Parvesh Kumar alias Mannu, Rams nephew, a juvenile, and his son Vishal Jangotra alias \"Shamma\".\r\n\r\nThe chargesheet also names investigating officers head constable Tilak Raj and Sub-Inspector Anand Dutta, who allegedly took Rs 4 lakh from Ram and destroyed crucial evidence.\r\n*\r\nThe issue of providing the accused copies of the \"challan\", or the chargesheet, was raised before the judge by the lawyers, Ankush Sharma, who is pleading the case for Sanji Ram, his son and others, told reporters.\r\n\r\nHe said the chargesheet was presented in court on April 9 but copies had not yet been provided.\r\n\r\nRam told the judge that they wanted narco tests and were ready for them.\r\n\r\nThe judge asked the accused whether they had been given copies of the chargesheet, which runs into 400 pages, added A K Sawahney, who is representing head constable Tilak Raj.\r\n*\r\nHe told reporters that Jammu and Kashmir Chief Minister Mehbooba Mufti had been talking about a fast track trial but copies of the chargesheet had still not been provided to them.\r\n\r\nIn a narco analysis test, the subject is injected with sodium pentothal or sodium amytal. The dose is dependent on the persons sex, age, health and physical condition.\r\n\r\nIt does not have any legal sanctity as evidence until a court gives permission to conduct these tests. The test only helps as corroborative and not as primary evidence, say legal experts.', '0', '2018-04-16', '2018-04-16 11:07:07', 'Active'),
(117, 20, 16, 60, 28, 'e576664bc406edbf89266b980a00b29d.jpeg', 'India\'s Yuki Bhambri returns to top-100 tennis rankings after more than 2 years.', 'India\'s tennis player Yuki Bhambri on Monday returned to top-100 for the first time since February 2016 on the back of his title-winning performance at the Taipei Challenger as he leapfrogged 22 places to a career-best rank of 83.\r\n\r\nThis is the best rank an Indian has achieved in ATP singles chart since Somdev Devvarman touched a career-high 62 in July 2011.\r\n*\r\nYuki had first broken into top-100 late in 2015 but injuries did not allow him to climb further. However, the resilient 25-year-old has worked his way back to top-100 which, if maintained, will allow him direct entry into the Grand Slams and the ATP 1000 series Masters event.\r\n\r\n\"It\'s only the beginning, I have to move up a lot more and I am looking forward to the challenge,\" Yuki told PTI.\r\n*\r\nAsked if top-50 was a realistic target for him, Yuki said, \"Not at the moment. Too far.\"\r\n\r\nYuki has always maintained that he has the game to challenge the best players and has proved with his recent big wins over world number 12 Lucas Puillee (Indian Wells, March 2018) and world number 22 Gael Monfils (Washington, August 2017).\r\n*\r\nHis Davis Cup teammate Ramkumar Ramanathan too rose to a career-best 116\r\nas he jumped 17 places after ending runner-up to Yuki in Taipei.\r\n\r\nSumit Nagal though lost two places to be 215 and was followed by Prajnesh Gunneswaran (266) and Arjun Kadhe (394).\r\n*\r\nIn the doubles, Divij Sharan further improved his career-best rank by moving up to 41, a gain of one place. Leander Paes, who became the most successful doubles player in Davis Cup, lost four places to be in 49th position.\r\n\r\nRohan Bopanna is leading the doubles chart for India at number 19.\r\n*\r\nMeanwhile, Ankita Raina too improved on her career-best rank as she jumped three places to 194 while Karman Kaur Thandi dropped a place to 268.\r\n\r\nIn the doubles, out of action Sania Mirza was unchanged at number 24.', '1', '2018-04-16', '2018-04-19 04:34:10', 'Active'),
(118, 20, 16, 60, 28, 'f94ac2298d072d8498292b08addc1663.jpeg', '\'Call papa over, want to hug him\' Ziva Dhoni said during MS Dhoni\'s blistering 7', 'Mahendra Singh Dhoni has millions of fans across the world and on Sunday they were witness to another master-class from the legend as Chennai Super Kings almost pulled off a heist over Kings XI Punjab in a tense encounter in Mohali on Sunday.\r\n\r\nDhoni battled back pain and scored a breathtaking 79 not out off only 44 balls but just could not manage to take his across the finish line at the PCA stadium in Mohali, but it was the home that prevailed on the night by 4 runs.\r\n*\r\nChasing a mammoth 198 for victory, Dhoni struck his career-best T20 score and even hit a six off the last ball of the match but Chennai still fell short of the target, managing to reach 193 for the loss of 5 wickets in 20 overs.\r\n*\r\nCSK needed 17 runs from the last over and Dhoni managed to knock off 12 of those with a boundary and a six. But Mohit Sharma, who bowled the high-pressure last over, had the last laugh.\r\nEven as Dhoni dazzled the cricketing world with his range of shots and kept CSK alive in a stiff chase with sixes and boundaries that brought back memories of old, Ziva was seen persuading someone to call her father over so she could hug him!\r\n*\r\nAfter the match, Dhoni was seen with his daughter Ziva, who was all smiles after her dad\'s heroic innings. Ziva had been an ardent supporter of CSK and is often seen in the stands with her mother Sakshi cheering together for the franchise.', '0', '2018-04-16', '2018-04-16 11:15:36', 'Active'),
(119, 20, 16, 60, 28, '4ddc5398710f6f63c7f352118e68eb36.jpeg', 'IGNOU Re-registration till May 31: Steps to apply.', 'The Indira Gandhi National Open University (IGNOU) has released the last date of re-registration for Bachelors, Master Degree and selected PG Diplomas programmes for the July 2018. The candidates interested for the re-registration may apply by May 31.\r\n\r\nThe registration is applicable for all students enrolled in undergraduate/postgraduate programmes of two-three year duration.\r\n\r\nThe candidates can re-register for the next year/semester of your Programme irrespective of whether they have submitted the assignments or appeared in the term-end examination of the previous semester.\r\n*\r\n    The first-time applicants have to click the available programme tab on the homepage of the online re-registration system\r\n    Select the desired programme and carefully read the course details (compulsory or electives), credits, lab, project work of programme including eligibility criteria, fee details, duration, et al.\r\n    On the homepage, click on \'Register yourself\' that appears in the applicant login area and fill the required registration details. Remember, enrolment number will be your username\r\n    While choosing your password, ensure that it is alphanumeric and between 8 to 16 characters long\r\n    After filling the mandatory information, click the Submit button\r\n    Your username will be instantly sent to you via e-mail and SMS\r\n*\r\nAbout IGNOU:\r\n\r\n    The Indira Gandhi National Open University (IGNOU), established by an Act of Parliament in 1985\r\n    The University began by offering two academic programmes in 1987, i.e., Diploma in Management and Diploma in Distance Education, with the strength of 4,528 students', '4', '2018-04-16', '2018-04-19 04:31:07', 'Active'),
(120, 20, 16, 65, 28, '615104005da9450c818fd5ba69f02837.jpeg', 'Audi reveals e-tron Vision Gran Turismo', 'Audi has pulled the wraps off its latest stunner, the e-tron Gran Turismo. The car was originally designed for the 15th anniversary of the Gran Turismo video game on the PlayStation 4. The design concept has turned into reality as a part of Audi\'s marketing campaign, built around its new e-tron electric car sub-brand.\r\n*\r\nAudi has stated that the latest four-wheel drive 816bhp electronic-powered supercar as a race taxi at selected Formula E events. The two-door supercar possibly hints at a zero-emission flagship being considered as a performance figurehead for the company\'s recently confirmed four door e-tron GT. The supercar is tipped to be placed at the top of the line-up which consists of pure electric production models which are due in the coming years.\r\n*\r\nConstructed at Ingolstadt, the one-off prototype has been planned to provide selected customers and guests of the German car maker with high-speed passenger rides during Formula E race weekends, starting in Rome from April 14, 2018.\r\n\r\nAs of now, Audi has confirmed three battery-powered e-tron models - the e-tron Quattro, the e-tron Sportback, and the e-tron GT.\r\n*\r\nSpeaking now for the e-tron Vision GT, the electric motors used in it will be based on the production unit all set for reveal in the upcoming production-spec e-ton Quattro. Three electric motors combine together to churn out 816bhp, a figure which Audi claims is sufficient to provide its latest 1,450kg coupe with a power-to-weight ratio of 563bhp per tonne.\r\n\r\n', '2', '2018-04-16', '2018-04-19 04:34:47', 'Active'),
(121, 20, 16, 60, 28, '8dbb2af71c9125789b3727870f6c69d3.jpg', 'OnePlus 6 new blue variant confirmed, in India Amazon likely to start selling it', 'Another day, another OnePlus 6 leak. The next OnePlus phone is likely to launch in May but ahead of the launch a new promotional banner of the phone is doing rounds on some Chinese websites. It reveals -- or rather confirms -- something that people have already guessed at: The OnePlus 6 will also come in a Coral Blue colour.\r\n\r\nAas expected, apart from the top hardware -- similar to what we have seen in the phones like the Xiaomi Mi Mix 2S and the Galaxy S9 this year -- the OnePlus 6 will also come with updated OnePlus software called Oxygen OS. This will be lightly modified Android Oreo. Although it will retain the look and feel of stock Android, the new Oxygen OS will likely come with gestures and features similar to those seen in the iPhone X earlier.\r\n*\r\nMeanwhile, a teaser video of the OnePlus 6 has also appeared which too confirms something obvious. The teaser video suggests that the OnePlus 6 will be exclusive to Amazon India as far as the Indian online market is concerned. Though the phone will also be available through OnePlus offline stores and the company\'s offline partners.\r\n*\r\nApart from the new colour, the banner reveals that the OnePlus 6 will come with two cameras on the back, with the primary camera using a 16-megapixel image sensor while the secondary camera using 20-megapixel sensor. The banner also lists some of the information that has already been confirmed by OnePlus. It notes that the OnePlus 6 will come with up to 8GB RAM and up to 256GB internal storage. It will be powered by Qualcomm Snapdragon 845 processor. The promotional banner also reveals that the OnePlus 6 will come with improved Dash charging that should help users recharge the battery of the OnePlus 6 even faster than what was possible with the OnePlus 5 or the OnePlus 5T.\r\n*\r\nAhead of the launch, a lot of OnePlus 6 details have been leaked. In fact, just last week the phone\'s full photos were leaked by a case maker. Although the phone was inside cases, some of these cases were transparent, which gave us a fairly good look at the device. The design of the OnePlus 6 is changing compared to that of the OnePlus 5T. The new OnePlus 6 is likely to come with the red slider button that controls the ringing and silent modes. This button is also likely to be used by OnePlus as the button to get focus when the camera app is on. Then there is the placement of the rear dual-cameras in the OnePlus 6. The camera module will be placed in the top middle of the rear cover, unlike on the right edge the way it is in the OnePlus 5T. Also, under the camera module there will be the fingerprint sensor.\r\n*\r\nThe OnePlus 6 is also coming with a screen -- likely to be 6.28 inches -- that has a notch. Although the company has suggested that the users will be able to hide the notch through software settings.\r\n*\r\nThe global launch of the OnePlus 6 is expected in May and there is a chance that the phone should come to India within a few days after the announcement. Basically, India will be among the first countries where the OnePlus 6 will go on sale given the fact that it is the company\'s largest market right now. There is no word on the price, although there is talk that the OnePlus 6 will be slightly more expensive that the OnePlus 5T. This \"slightly\" could be Rs 2,000 to Rs 3000, although the top variant of OnePlus 6 (8GB RAM and 256GB storage) may cost close to Rs 50,000 in India. The starting price could be around Rs 35,000.', '5', '2018-04-16', '2018-04-20 15:02:59', 'Active'),
(122, 22, 4, 23, 28, '14f0f80cd918b65fcac4c4be42f77ea7.jpeg', 'BJP claims 4 lakh crore of NPAs, RBI figures separate.', 'Many leaders of the Bharatiya Janata Party tweeted that the Rs 9 lakh-crore NPA or stranded debt that the UPA government had given to him, of which Rs 4 lakh crore has been recovered by the BJP government. But the statistics of the Reserve Bank are presenting a different story. According to this, only 29 thousand crore rupees have been recovered in the last four years.\r\n*\r\nAccording to the Indian Express, some BJP leaders tweeted on Saturday, claiming that under the \'Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code\' (IBC) 4 lakh crore NPAs have been recovered. The loan of about Rs 9 lakh crore given to the corporate by the UPA government was transformed into NPA or stranded debt, from which it has been recovered.\r\n*\r\nBut the latest data from the Reserve Bank shows that in the years 2016-17 and 2017-18 (till December), public banks have recovered only 15,786 crore rupees. These include recovery from all the media including IBC. The banks started recovery after January 2017 under IBC. \r\n*\r\nAccording to the data, 21 public banks in the last four financial years (2014-2018) have been able to recover only Rs 29,343 crore. In the meantime, the banks put the debt of Rs 2.72 lakh crores in the write-off, i.e. right-off.\r\n\r\nThese data from the Reserve Bank were given by Finance Minister Shiv Pratap Shukla on March 27 in the Rajya Sabha. During this period, 89 per cent of non-performing assets (NPAs) of public banks were not realized and they had to be put off in the account.\r\n*\r\nActually, in case of loans under IBC, the debtor gets the opportunity to resolve the matter within 180 days and increase the deadline to further 90 days. ', '2', '2018-04-16', '2018-04-18 05:30:28', 'Active'),
